Use all five senses. Keep sentences short in a helpful series.

1167
01:31:50,000 --> 01:31:55,120
Stay serious about sharing similar ideas through simple study skills.

1168
01:31:55,120 --> 01:32:00,960
Identify the source for special data and any specific speech forms.

1169
01:32:00,960 --> 01:32:03,120
State each statement with structure.

1170
01:32:03,120 --> 01:32:07,040
Define success and celebrate successful steps.

1171
01:32:07,040 --> 01:32:12,159
Choose suitable evidence. Write a summary to support each task.

1172
01:32:12,159 --> 01:32:18,159
Theory guides topics. Training and practice reveal useful truths we understand.

1173
01:32:18,159 --> 01:32:24,400
Our understanding grows each unit. Group work stays useful and varied.

1174
01:32:24,400 --> 01:32:36,000
In my view, vocabulary grows through daily writing and mindful reading. We accompany classmates, acknowledge help and admire appropriate approaches.

1175
01:32:36,000 --> 01:32:39,120
Do not assume meanings. Pay attention.

1176
01:32:39,120 --> 01:32:45,440
Keep an aware attitude. Always combine notes. Communicate questions.

1177
01:32:45,440 --> 01:32:50,239
Avoid confusion. Connect ideas clearly.

1178
01:32:50,239 --> 01:32:59,679
A strong argument can convince while calm breathing helps us cope. According to the teacher, we already covered this chapter thoroughly.

1179
01:32:59,679 --> 01:33:05,040
Do not annoy others. Phones are banned inside this quiet area.

1180
01:33:05,040 --> 01:33:10,800
Birth stories in literature show breath, life, and careful choices.

1181
01:33:10,800 --> 01:33:16,239
Cigarette ads are banned. Common sense and consideration matter on campus.

1182
01:33:16,239 --> 01:33:19,440
Our county library kept covered shelves.

1183
01:33:19,440 --> 01:33:22,719
The curve display looked elegant.

1184
01:33:22,719 --> 01:33:27,760
I will definitely overcome difficulty during study and practical labs.

1185
01:33:27,760 --> 01:33:34,560
We educate new members. Educated mentors guide us kindly or else we struggle.

1186
01:33:34,560 --> 01:33:39,920
When we encounter an error, expected steps include calm review.

1187
01:33:39,920 --> 01:33:45,280
Experiments can be expensive. A feather burned when we tested flame.

1188
01:33:45,280 --> 01:33:47,760
The wooden frame broke. A gap appeared.

1189
01:33:47,760 --> 01:33:49,600
We fixed it quickly.

1190
01:33:49,600 --> 01:33:54,719
Strange things happen. Hey, that household incident brought new insight.

1191
01:33:54,719 --> 01:33:57,280
January workshops are leading events.

1192
01:33:57,280 --> 01:34:00,080
Living here changed my manner.

1193
01:34:00,080 --> 01:34:06,800
Mathematics uses meters. Math's problems appear mostly with careful units.

1194
01:34:06,800 --> 01:34:11,760
The needle broke. Numerous tools helped during the opening session.

1195
01:34:11,760 --> 01:34:28,400
I opposed a rushed outline. A penny of patience saves time. Permanent records include pipe damage reports and priest donations. Surprisingly, each pupil planned a purchase. We reached the reader award list.

1196
01:34:28,400 --> 01:34:33,360
A regular response after rugby training mentions injury and recovery.

1197
01:34:33,360 --> 01:34:37,840
Our sector meeting happened under shade after a short shower.

1198
01:34:37,840 --> 01:34:43,280
The site looked solid. Recent spending spread across such projects.

1199
01:34:43,280 --> 01:34:49,600
That tale won the third prize. The judge loved the emotional touch.

1200
01:34:49,600 --> 01:34:54,639
I solved the problem twice. Success was unlikely at that venue.

1201
01:34:54,639 --> 01:35:01,840
We weigh ideas fairly. One winner gets a yellow ribbon.

1202
01:35:01,840 --> 01:35:07,679
Rose, our teacher, asked us to introduce ourselves again before class begins.

1203
01:35:07,679 --> 01:35:18,320
Yes, Nick. She said this exercise will feature our speaking skill clearly. I noted her words carefully and I will perform the task with confidence.

1204
01:35:18,320 --> 01:35:23,520
Sometimes small issues arise but we cope and still achieve results.

1205
01:35:23,520 --> 01:35:27,760
The professor showed a figure on the screen to explain the concept.

1206
01:35:27,760 --> 01:35:32,239
He also mentioned different regions of the country in geography.

1207
01:35:32,239 --> 01:35:37,840
I believe understanding relationships between ideas is an important resource.

1208
01:35:37,840 --> 01:35:44,159
Absolutely. Knowledge itself is a resource that helps us reach higher goals.

1209
01:35:44,159 --> 01:35:49,760
The teacher explained that every option in an exam question has meaning.

1210
01:35:49,760 --> 01:35:54,880
Yes, we must not exceed the time limit or the grade will fall.

1211
01:35:54,880 --> 01:35:59,920
Our science experiment produced a result that was better than expected.

1212
01:35:59,920 --> 01:36:06,159
That result proved our skills are developing with practice and patience.

1213
01:36:06,159 --> 01:36:10,320
The school announced a ban on phones during study hours.

1214
01:36:10,320 --> 01:36:15,600
I agree with that rule. 1 meter of distance helps reduce distraction.

1215
01:36:15,600 --> 01:36:22,000
Finally, I admire how every feature of our education builds strong character.

1216
01:36:22,000 --> 01:36:31,600
Me too, Nick. With skill, effort, and motivation, we will succeed in the future.

1217
01:36:31,600 --> 01:36:41,040
Rose, do you want to play a sport this weekend? Yes, Nick. I like sport. What game do you want to play? Football or basketball?

1218
01:36:41,040 --> 01:36:50,480
Maybe soccer. Some people call it football and some call it soccer. We can play with a team and try to score a goal.

1219
01:36:50,480 --> 01:36:56,400
That sounds fun. We will need a ball, a net, and maybe even a referee.

1220
01:36:56,400 --> 01:37:04,800
Tom can help. He likes to be the coach, and he can train the players to kick, throw, and catch the ball.

1221
01:37:04,800 --> 01:37:13,199
I can run very fast, but I cannot jump very high. If we play basketball, I will probably lose the match.

1222
01:37:13,199 --> 01:37:20,639
Winning or losing is not important. The main point is to enjoy the activity and get some practice.

1223
01:37:20,639 --> 01:37:28,400
True. We can also try tennis. I have a racket and you can borrow my bat or golf club.

1224
01:37:28,400 --> 01:37:36,880
Wow, you have so many things. Tennis, baseball, golf. You must enjoy every game.

1225
01:37:36,880 --> 01:37:43,600
I do. Sometimes I go swimming at the stadium pool or I exercise in the gym.

1226
01:37:43,600 --> 01:37:51,199
Good idea. Maybe today we can go to the track and field near the stadium. We can run a race together.

1227
01:37:51,199 --> 01:38:01,280
Yes, let's do that. A small competition will be exciting and it will be good exercise for both of us.

1228
01:38:01,280 --> 01:38:05,600
Rose, what hobbies do you usually enjoy at home?

1229
01:38:05,600 --> 01:38:14,080
I like drawing and painting. I sometimes design pictures and I also enjoy photography with my camera.

1230
01:38:14,080 --> 01:38:20,639
That is interesting. I often watch your photo blog and your video posts are very creative.

1231
01:38:20,639 --> 01:38:27,199
Thank you, Nick. I also love music. I can sing songs and I play the guitar and piano.

1232
01:38:27,199 --> 01:38:33,760
Really? I only know how to play the drum. Maybe we can start a small band together.

1233
01:38:33,760 --> 01:38:39,119
Yes. And we can perform in the school concert or at the local festival.

1234
01:38:39,119 --> 01:38:45,920
Besides music, do you enjoy other hobbies like craft, knitting, or sewing?

1235
01:38:45,920 --> 01:38:52,800
I tried knitting once, but I prefer cooking and baking. I also like gardening and planting flowers.

1236
01:38:52,800 --> 01:39:01,760
That sounds nice. I usually relax by reading novels, writing in my diary, or posting ideas on my blog.

1237
01:39:01,760 --> 01:39:08,880
Those are wonderful activities. They help us express our feelings and use our imagination.

1238
01:39:08,880 --> 01:39:15,840
Yes, hobbies bring joy, memory, and confidence. They are a special part of life.

1239
01:39:15,840 --> 01:39:23,840
I agree, Nick. Every hobby is a chance to learn and to feel pleasure.

1240
01:39:23,840 --> 01:39:28,000
Rose, do you usually watch television in your free time?

1241
01:39:28,000 --> 01:39:30,320
Yes, I watch different channels.

1242
01:39:30,320 --> 01:39:34,800
Sometimes I enjoy a cartoon, a drama, or a comedy show.

1243
01:39:34,800 --> 01:39:43,119
I prefer the news and educational programs. I also read magazines and newspapers to get more information.

1244
01:39:43,119 --> 01:39:49,280
That is useful. I often listen to the radio or check websites and apps on the internet.

1245
01:39:49,280 --> 01:39:58,080
Do you watch videos online? Many people like to download or upload movies and then share them with friends.

1246
01:39:58,080 --> 01:40:07,440
Yes, I watch, listen, and even post comments. I sometimes chat, send messages, and like or share posts.

1247
01:40:07,440 --> 01:40:15,280
Social media is powerful. People can follow celebrities, and every audience or viewer can give their opinion.

1248
01:40:15,280 --> 01:40:22,800
True fans enjoy entertainment, but media also shows advertisements and announcements.

1249
01:40:22,800 --> 01:40:31,360
Yes, advertising is everywhere. Still, I appreciate good communication and interesting discussion online.

1250
01:40:31,360 --> 01:40:38,080
Me too. But sometimes too much media can confuse people with too much information.

1251
01:40:38,080 --> 01:40:45,520
That is right. We should use technology carefully and only choose what is relevant and useful.

1252
01:40:45,520 --> 01:40:54,800
Yes, Nick, balance is important. Media should entertain us but also help us learn.

1253
01:40:54,800 --> 01:40:59,040
Rose, do you want to go out with our friends this weekend?

1254
01:40:59,040 --> 01:41:03,360
Yes, Nick. Maybe we can join a party or a concert.

1255
01:41:03,360 --> 01:41:10,560
That sounds exciting. A music festival is happening in the city. There will be a band on stage.

1256
01:41:10,560 --> 01:41:17,520
Great. I enjoy every performance. The theater near the market is also showing a new comedy.

1257
01:41:17,520 --> 01:41:23,920
We have many options. We can go to the cinema, the theater, or just walk around town.

1258
01:41:23,920 --> 01:41:29,840
I would like to join the local event. It is a good occasion to meet neighbors and friends.

1259
01:41:29,840 --> 01:41:42,000
True. Public events bring the community together and they create a social connection. I feel joy when the audience laughs and I admire the enthusiasm of every performer.

1260
01:41:42,000 --> 01:41:50,080
People show their style and fashion at these events. Some wear modern clothes, others prefer traditional.

1261
01:41:50,080 --> 01:41:58,080
Yes, appearance is important for some, but for me, the main purpose is to have fun and share moments.

1262
01:41:58,080 --> 01:42:05,679
I agree. Music, drama, and art entertain us, but they also support culture and society.

1263
01:42:05,679 --> 01:42:13,360
And joining with friends gives us more confidence, pleasure, and wonderful memories.

1264
01:42:13,360 --> 01:42:19,440
Rose, do you think hobbies and free time are as important as work and study?

1265
01:42:19,440 --> 01:42:28,239
Yes, Nick, I believe so. Free time gives us energy and confidence to face assignments and projects.

1266
01:42:28,239 --> 01:42:43,920
True. At university, I often receive an assignment or a training task and I must concentrate to finish it. I also attend conferences and discussions where we analyze ideas and share different methods.

1267
01:42:43,920 --> 01:42:49,840
Study can be tough, but practice and organization help us manage every challenge.

1268
01:42:49,840 --> 01:43:04,800
I agree. When I feel stress, I try to relax and find a solution. Balance is important. Work and hobbies should combine. Exercise, art or reading can support the learning process.

1269
01:43:04,800 --> 01:43:13,679
Yes, they bring benefits and value. They also prove that knowledge is not only from books but also from experience.

1270
01:43:13,679 --> 01:43:21,679
I sometimes imagine my future career. I want to be professional but I also want time for leisure.

1271
01:43:21,679 --> 01:43:30,000
That is a wise opinion. Success should include purpose, joy, and respect for yourself and others.

1272
01:43:30,000 --> 01:43:39,600
You are right. Life is not only about results. It is also about trust, support, and positive relationships.

1273
01:43:39,600 --> 01:43:49,920
Exactly. Free time, hobbies, and study must all remain in balance to create a happy life.

1274
01:43:49,920 --> 01:43:54,960
Rose, do you want to spend some free time outside in nature?

1275
01:43:54,960 --> 01:44:00,560
Yes, Nick. I love nature. Let's go walking near the river or climb a small mountain.

1276
01:44:00,560 --> 01:44:07,360
Good idea. We can sit under a tree, look at the green leaves, and enjoy the fresh air.

1277
01:44:07,360 --> 01:44:13,520
I like gardening, too. Planting flowers makes me feel peace, and it reduces stress.

1278
01:44:13,520 --> 01:44:20,320
The ocean is also beautiful. Watching the waves and listening to the wind brings relief.

1279
01:44:20,320 --> 01:44:29,360
True. Every season is special. In spring, the flowers bloom. In summer, the sun is strong.

1280
01:44:29,360 --> 01:44:35,600
In autumn, the colors change. And in winter, we sometimes see snow and ice.

1281
01:44:35,600 --> 01:44:43,040
Yes, I remember last winter. It was cold, but walking outside gave me joy and energy.

1282
01:44:43,040 --> 01:44:50,639
Nature gives us plenty of chances to relax. A short trip or a tour can make life wonderful.

1283
01:44:50,639 --> 01:44:57,360
I agree. Even a small picnic outside is a great opportunity to feel free and happy.

1284
01:44:57,360 --> 01:45:04,560
Then let's organize an outdoor activity soon. It will be simple but full of pleasure.

1285
01:45:04,560 --> 01:45:12,159
Yes, Nick. Being close to nature always brings us comfort and delight.

1286
01:45:12,159 --> 01:45:21,520
Rose, after talking about sports, hobbies, media, and nature, what do you think is the main benefit of free time?

1287
01:45:21,520 --> 01:45:29,600
I think free time helps us appreciate life. It gives us energy, confidence, and positive feelings.

1288
01:45:29,600 --> 01:45:37,440
Yes, I agree. Free time activities also prove that joy and learning can exist together.

1289
01:45:37,440 --> 01:45:46,800
Exactly. Every hobby brings value and purpose. Some are artistic, some are physical, but all are important.

1290
01:45:46,800 --> 01:45:54,719
We also discover new interests and we combine fun with knowledge. That is a great opportunity.

1291
01:45:54,719 --> 01:46:02,960
True, modern life is busy, but it is essential to organize time for leisure and relaxation.

1292
01:46:02,960 --> 01:46:11,840
Yes, balance is fundamental. Work and study are important, but hobbies protect our health and spirit.

1293
01:46:11,840 --> 01:46:18,159
And when we share activities with friends, we create memories, respect, and trust.

1294
01:46:18,159 --> 01:46:25,199
Free time is not a waste. It is a wonderful part of life that helps us remain strong.

1295
01:46:25,199 --> 01:46:42,719
Yes, Nick. In every generation, free time and hobbies will always have a special place. Rose, last week in March, I joined a poetry reading at the local library. The author read a poem on stage, and it was very dramatic.

1296
01:46:42,719 --> 01:46:49,040
That sounds wonderful. In February, I visited a small museum in a rural town.

1297
01:46:49,040 --> 01:46:56,480
They showed old-fashioned jewelry, clothes, and even farming tools like a curved pot and a motorcart.

1298
01:46:56,480 --> 01:47:08,239
Interesting. I once saw a photo of an earthquake exhibition. The display explained how dust, rocks, and sudden movement can change a mountain in only one moment.

1299
01:47:08,239 --> 01:47:18,800
Yes, nature is powerful. Sometimes people feel ashamed or afraid, but disasters also teach us important lessons about safety.

1300
01:47:18,800 --> 01:47:28,159
True. By the way, my neighbor always bakes biscuits in her oven. The smell is amazing, and she always offers me a piece to taste.

1301
01:47:28,159 --> 01:47:37,199
That makes me hungry. I like simple food too, but sometimes I prefer something special like a cake for an annual festival.

1302
01:47:37,199 --> 01:47:46,960
Do you remember our retired coach? He told us that confidence and patience are fundamental for every individual not only in sport but in life.

1303
01:47:46,960 --> 01:48:07,520
Yes. And he said every generation must appreciate knowledge, communicate clearly and respect others. I still remember his advice. Yesterday I met a junior student. He was annoyed because he had to repeat a tough assignment. But I told him to concentrate and believe in himself.

1304
01:48:07,520 --> 01:48:16,080
Good advice. Life can seem difficult, but if we manage carefully and remain positive, every problem has a solution.

1305
01:48:16,080 --> 01:48:27,199
Exactly. Whether it is a shadow in the evening, a sudden flash of light, or a new invention, every small detail can delight us.

1306
01:48:27,199 --> 01:48:37,360
I agree, Nick. Free time, hobbies, and even these little experiences all belong to our memory and make life richer.

1307
01:48:37,360 --> 01:48:42,400
Rose, you look a little sick today. Do you want to see a doctor?

1308
01:48:42,400 --> 01:48:48,719
Yes, Nick. I already booked an appointment at the clinic. The nurse told me to come this afternoon.

1309
01:48:48,719 --> 01:48:53,920
Good. If the doctor thinks it is serious, you may need to visit the hospital.

1310
01:48:53,920 --> 01:48:59,920
I hope not. Last time the dentist gave me a tablet and some medicine from the pharmacy.

1311
01:48:59,920 --> 01:49:05,199
Was it for your toothache? I remember you had pain in your mouth and throat.

1312
01:49:05,199 --> 01:49:08,400
Yes, it was terrible.

1313
01:49:08,400 --> 01:49:11,920
The dentist gave me pills and told me to rest.

1314
01:49:11,920 --> 01:49:14,239
Did they give you an injection?

1315
01:49:14,239 --> 01:49:18,960
Sometimes a small drug helps to cure the problem quickly.

1316
01:49:18,960 --> 01:49:26,960
No injection this time, but the patient before me had a fever, so the doctor used a thermometer to check her temperature.

1317
01:49:26,960 --> 01:49:33,360
That makes sense. Many people catch a virus these days and infection spreads easily.

1318
01:49:33,360 --> 01:49:41,119
True. If my condition gets worse, I will ask for treatment, maybe even a bandage if I get hurt.

1319
01:49:41,119 --> 01:49:47,440
Don't worry, Rose. I will go with you to the clinic. It is better to be safe than sorry.

1320
01:49:47,440 --> 01:49:54,960
Thank you, Nick. Good health is the most important thing for every person.

1321
01:49:54,960 --> 01:50:00,639
Rose, when you think about health, which part of the body do you worry about most?

1322
01:50:00,639 --> 01:50:07,520
For me, the heart and lungs are the most important. If they are strong, the whole body feels fit.

1323
01:50:07,520 --> 01:50:10,639
I agree. The brain controls everything.

1324
01:50:10,639 --> 01:50:15,040
But if the heart or stomach has a problem, you really feel weak.

1325
01:50:15,040 --> 01:50:23,119
Yes. Even skin, bones, and muscles need care. Last year, I broke a bone in my arm near the elbow.

1326
01:50:23,119 --> 01:50:26,080
Ouch. Did it hurt a lot?

1327
01:50:26,080 --> 01:50:32,480
Yes. I could not move my shoulder or hand. Even my fingers and thumb felt painful.

1328
01:50:32,480 --> 01:50:40,560
I once injured my leg. The knee and ankle swelled and I could not walk on my foot or move my toes.

1329
01:50:40,560 --> 01:50:50,560
That sounds terrible. I also had back pain once. The doctor said it was because I sat too long and my chest muscles were not strong enough.

1330
01:50:50,560 --> 01:50:54,080
That's why exercise is important.

1331
01:50:54,080 --> 01:51:04,320
It helps every part of the body. Head, neck, eyes, ears, nose, mouth, teeth, and even the throat and tongue.

1332
01:51:04,320 --> 01:51:10,080
True. I wear glasses to help my sight, but I still try to protect my eyes.

1333
01:51:10,080 --> 01:51:18,159
Good idea. And we should measure our height and weight regularly to know if we are healthy, too thin, or too heavy.

1334
01:51:18,159 --> 01:51:27,199
Yes. And sleep is also important. If I don't rest well, I feel dizzy, tired, and sleepy the next day.

1335
01:51:27,199 --> 01:51:34,000
Same here. I get hungry and thirsty quickly when I don't take care of myself.

1336
01:51:34,000 --> 01:51:42,480
Nick, the whole body works together. If one part suffers, the rest also feels it.

1337
01:51:42,480 --> 01:51:48,400
Rose, have you ever seen an ambulance rushing through the street with its siren?

1338
01:51:48,400 --> 01:51:55,599
Yes, Nick. Last week, it was an emergency and the patient inside looked unconscious.

1339
01:51:55,599 --> 01:52:02,400
That's scary. Sometimes an operation or surgery is needed very quickly to save a life.

1340
01:52:02,400 --> 01:52:12,960
True. My neighbor once had a serious injury from a car crash. He had a deep cut on his leg, a bruise on his back, and even a burn on his arm.

1341
01:52:12,960 --> 01:52:14,719
Did he bleed a lot?

1342
01:52:14,719 --> 01:52:22,719
Yes. And the doctors had to stop the bleeding fast. They used bandages and gave him strong treatment.

1343
01:52:22,719 --> 01:52:31,199
I imagine he was in shock. When people are afraid, their spirit feels weak and they can suffer from fear and anxiety.

1344
01:52:31,199 --> 01:52:39,760
Yes. And stress or depression can follow after an accident. The mental pain is sometimes harder than the physical wound.

1345
01:52:39,760 --> 01:52:46,080
That is true. Dangerous situations always affect both the body and the mind.

1346
01:52:46,080 --> 01:52:54,159
Some people smoke when they feel nervous, but smoking is harmful and can even cause lung disease or poison the body.

1347
01:52:54,159 --> 01:53:01,840
Exactly. We must defend ourselves against harmful habits and try to live safe and healthy lives.

1348
01:53:01,840 --> 01:53:09,840
Life is fragile. One moment you are alive and strong and the next moment you may fall and feel helpless.

1349
01:53:09,840 --> 01:53:12,880
That's why rescue teams are important.

1350
01:53:12,880 --> 01:53:16,719
They work to save people and protect the community.

1351
01:53:16,719 --> 01:53:27,760
Yes, Nick. Emergencies remind us how precious life is and why health and safety must always come first.

1352
01:53:27,760 --> 01:53:38,400
Rose, how do you usually feel during a busy week? Honestly, Nick, sometimes I feel tired, hungry, and thirsty before lunchtime.

1353
01:53:38,400 --> 01:53:46,239
Same here. If I don't sleep enough, I feel sleepy all day, and I may even fall asleep in class.

1354
01:53:46,239 --> 01:53:52,080
Yes. When I am asleep at the wrong time, I wake up dizzy and weak.

1355
01:53:52,080 --> 01:53:59,280
Do you ever sneeze a lot in spring? I have an allergy to pollen and it makes my nose red.

1356
01:53:59,280 --> 01:54:08,880
Oh, yes. I get a sore throat and sometimes a cough. The symptoms make me feel ill, but luckily it is not a serious disease.

1357
01:54:08,880 --> 01:54:15,119
When I get a headache or stomach ache, I usually take a pill and rest in bed.

1358
01:54:15,119 --> 01:54:21,599
That is a good method. Rest gives comfort to the body and helps us recover faster.

1359
01:54:21,599 --> 01:54:29,840
But stress is harder. It can cause anger, doubt, and even depression if we don't control our emotions.

1360
01:54:29,840 --> 01:54:38,719
True. Emotional health is as important as physical health. We must take care of our mental condition.

1361
01:54:38,719 --> 01:54:45,440
My grandma always says, "A calm spirit and a strong heart can protect you more than medicine."

1362
01:54:45,440 --> 01:54:56,159
I agree, Nick. Health is not only about the body, but also about feelings, thoughts, and peace of mind.

1363
01:54:56,159 --> 01:55:00,960
Rose, what do you usually do to stay fit and strong?

1364
01:55:00,960 --> 01:55:09,840
I exercise three times a week. Running and stretching help my muscles and I sometimes go to therapy sessions for my back.

1365
01:55:09,840 --> 01:55:29,199
That's smart. I tend to play sports, but I also depend on a healthy diet. If I eat too much, I gain weight. And if I eat too little, I feel weak. Yes, balance is important. Decreasing sugar and avoiding harmful food can prevent disease.

1366
01:55:29,199 --> 01:55:31,280
Do you drink alcohol?

1367
01:55:31,280 --> 01:55:37,520
No, I avoid alcoholic drinks. They can damage the liver and affect mental health.

1368
01:55:37,520 --> 01:55:45,119
I agree. Smoking is also dangerous. It causes stress on the lungs and decrease his lifespan.

1369
01:55:45,119 --> 01:55:53,119
True. The doctor once demonstrated with a scan how smoke can harm the lung. It was a shocking image.

1370
01:55:53,119 --> 01:55:59,599
That must have been scary. Do you think therapy and counseling are useful for stress?

1371
01:55:59,599 --> 01:56:05,760
Yes, therapy helps people control anxiety, depression, and emotional pain.

1372
01:56:05,760 --> 01:56:08,400
It brings comfort and relief.

1373
01:56:08,400 --> 01:56:16,639
I also try farming vegetables in my small garden. Fresh food makes me feel alive and full of energy.

1374
01:56:16,639 --> 01:56:26,960
That's a brilliant habit, Nick. Healthy lifestyle choices are the best medicine to protect both body and mind.

1375
01:56:26,960 --> 01:56:34,320
Rose, in our curriculum at school, health is always taught in the context of daily life.

1376
01:56:34,320 --> 01:56:42,000
Yes, I remember a debate last week. We had to define health and give a clear definition with examples.

1377
01:56:42,000 --> 01:56:48,800
The teacher demonstrated with data and illustrations how stress can affect both mental and physical health.

1378
01:56:48,800 --> 01:56:59,520
I liked that cultural habits also contribute to health. For instance, in some places people farm fresh food while in others they depend on processed meals.

1379
01:56:59,520 --> 01:57:03,199
True. Environmental factors matter too.

1380
01:57:03,199 --> 01:57:07,840
Pollution, smoke, and even nuclear tests can be harmful.

1381
01:57:07,840 --> 01:57:18,159
That's scary. In contrast, our neighborhood is safe and peaceful. I often see fellow students gather at midnight to study together.

1382
01:57:18,159 --> 01:57:27,520
Really, I would fall asleep by then. But sometimes crazy circumstances make people do unusual things.

1383
01:57:27,520 --> 01:57:35,440
Do you remember the ad on TV about a bride running in a wedding dress at midnight? It was funny, but also a bit silly.

1384
01:57:35,440 --> 01:57:42,320
Yes, I saw it. She tripped on a carpet, dropped her purple flowers, and looked embarrassed.

1385
01:57:42,320 --> 01:57:51,440
Haha. I also saw an illustration in a magazine of a prince trying to shake hands with everybody. It was humorous, but unrealistic.

1386
01:57:51,440 --> 01:58:00,159
Some people still swear that modern ads are brilliant, but others complain that advertisements constantly demand attention.

1387
01:58:00,159 --> 01:58:01,840
Exactly.

1388
01:58:01,840 --> 01:58:09,119
Feedback is important. Without it, companies may deliver poor service and damage their reputation.

1389
01:58:09,119 --> 01:58:15,679
True. In overall health research, even a small sample of data can reveal a lot.

1390
01:58:15,679 --> 01:58:20,400
Yes. Every bit of information contributes to the final conclusion.

1391
01:58:20,400 --> 01:58:32,639
Life is full of contrast. Sometimes painful, sometimes wonderful. But I believe if we are wise, patient, and willing, we can solve any problem.

1392
01:58:32,639 --> 01:58:43,920
I agree, Nick. Whatever the circumstance, we must remain strong, secure, and ready to help somebody in need.

1393
01:58:43,920 --> 01:58:50,719
Rose, yesterday at the gym, I forgot my towel. It was so unpleasant after exercise.

1394
01:58:50,719 --> 01:58:57,920
Oh, no. I always pack mine. I even keep extra underwear in my bag just in case.

1395
01:58:57,920 --> 01:59:07,440
Smart idea. My fellow trainer once gave me a suggestion to prepare a small plastic bottle for water and a steel container for snacks.

1396
01:59:07,440 --> 01:59:18,480
That's useful. Last month, I climbed a mount with friends. At nearly 30 minutes up the hill, I felt weak, but after 60 minutes, I was fine.

1397
01:59:18,480 --> 01:59:23,599
Wow, that's tough. Did you see anybody else on the track?

1398
01:59:23,599 --> 01:59:31,520
Yes. Somebody was carrying a tank of gear for camping. It was a bit crazy but impressive.

1399
01:59:31,520 --> 01:59:42,000
Haha, that reminds me of my neighbor. He once shook his arms so strongly in the garden that people thought he was doing military training.

1400
01:59:42,000 --> 01:59:50,480
People sometimes do silly things, but overall these little stories are humorous and give us joy.

1401
01:59:50,480 --> 02:00:12,000
True. Life can be ordinary or brilliant, but what matters is how we react and how we share moments. Exactly, Nick. Health, habits, and even these small experiences all belong to us. The choice is always yours.

1402
02:00:12,000 --> 02:00:22,159
Rose, what kind of work do you enjoy the most? Nick, I enjoy my job at the office because I work with a friendly team and helpful colleagues.

1403
02:00:22,159 --> 02:00:27,040
That sounds nice. Do you get along well with your boss and manager?

1404
02:00:27,040 --> 02:00:35,520
Yes, the manager is kind and the director is very professional. They respect every employee and worker in the company.

1405
02:00:35,520 --> 02:00:53,760
Good leaders make a big difference. In my career, I once had an employer who treated staff badly and many people left. That's sad. Right now, I feel lucky because my partner at work supports me and my secretary and assistant help with daily tasks.

1406
02:00:53,760 --> 02:00:59,760
What about your friends? I heard your brother is an engineer and your cousin is a lawyer.

1407
02:00:59,760 --> 02:01:08,400
That's right. My uncle is a doctor and my aunt is a nurse. I even have a neighbor who is a teacher and her husband is a professor.

1408
02:01:08,400 --> 02:01:16,719
Wow. So many jobs in your family. My father is a driver and my grandfather was a farmer.

1409
02:01:16,719 --> 02:01:23,760
My friend is a builder and her partner is an architect. They often work with a designer on new houses.

1410
02:01:23,760 --> 02:01:29,360
I also know a scientist who studies plants and an artist who paints portraits.

1411
02:01:29,360 --> 02:01:38,000
That's interesting. Last month, I met an actor at the theater, a cleaner at the cinema, and a waiter and waitress at a restaurant.

1412
02:01:38,000 --> 02:01:45,040
Don't forget the cook and the chef. They prepare delicious food and everyone appreciates them.

1413
02:01:45,040 --> 02:01:52,560
True. My cousin is an accountant. My neighbor is a banker and one of my old classmates became a politician.

1414
02:01:52,560 --> 02:02:01,199
That shows how many different jobs exist in the world. Each career has its own role and responsibility.

1415
02:02:01,199 --> 02:02:11,599
Yes, Nick. No matter if you are a worker, a manager, or a teacher, every job is important for society.

1416
02:02:11,599 --> 02:02:16,480
Rose, do you prefer working in a small shop or in a big company?

1417
02:02:16,480 --> 02:02:24,960
I think I prefer a company. A shop or store is nice, but a large firm or factory offers more career opportunities.

1418
02:02:24,960 --> 02:02:34,880
True. The business world is wide. Every industry needs people to complete projects, run programs, and finish tasks.

1419
02:02:34,880 --> 02:02:36,159
Yes.

1420
02:02:36,159 --> 02:02:41,280
And every worker has a duty, a role, and a responsibility.

1421
02:02:41,280 --> 02:02:44,880
Have you ever applied for a new position?

1422
02:02:44,880 --> 02:02:53,360
Yes, I once had an interview. I sent my application with my resume and CV. After training, I got the job.

1423
02:02:53,360 --> 02:02:56,639
That's good. Did you ever get a promotion?

1424
02:02:56,639 --> 02:03:01,679
Not yet, but my boss told me it might happen soon if I keep improving.

1425
02:03:01,679 --> 02:03:09,920
In my last company, I was part of a committee. The chairman led meetings about corporate strategy and financial plans.

1426
02:03:09,920 --> 02:03:17,679
That sounds important. In my department, we work in small divisions and every colleague depends on teamwork.

1427
02:03:17,679 --> 02:03:24,719
I once attended a commercial conference where business leaders discussed employment and consumer needs.

1428
02:03:24,719 --> 02:03:32,880
Yes, business is not only about selling products. It is also about people, leadership and responsibility.

1429
02:03:32,880 --> 02:03:44,080
Exactly, Rose. A successful business grows when it respects workers, managers, and consumers equally.

1430
02:03:44,080 --> 02:03:48,800
Rose, how often do you attend a meeting at your office?

1431
02:03:48,800 --> 02:03:56,800
Almost every week, Nick. Sometimes it is a small meeting and sometimes it is a big conference with presentations.

1432
02:03:56,800 --> 02:04:00,639
Do you usually have a deadline after the presentation?

1433
02:04:00,639 --> 02:04:08,639
Yes, we often get a schedule with clear dates. Every task must be finished on time and we must submit a report.

1434
02:04:08,639 --> 02:04:12,880
That sounds strict. How do you prepare your documents?

1435
02:04:12,880 --> 02:04:19,760
I usually organize every file and folder. I keep my papers in order with each page numbered.

1436
02:04:19,760 --> 02:04:33,679
Good idea. I also use a notepad and a diary to write notes. My calendar helps me remember meetings. On my desk, I always keep a book, some pens and pencils, and a stapler with clips.

1437
02:04:33,679 --> 02:04:35,920
Do you still send letters?

1438
02:04:35,920 --> 02:04:43,920
Sometimes I put the letter in an envelope, but mostly I use email or an office card with my ID and badge.

1439
02:04:43,920 --> 02:04:51,760
Yes, digital communication is faster, but we still need keys and locks to keep documents safe.

1440
02:04:51,760 --> 02:04:57,599
That's true. At the last meeting, I had to describe our project in detail.

1441
02:04:57,599 --> 02:05:01,599
Did you also design a chart or display for the discussion?

1442
02:05:01,599 --> 02:05:07,199
Yes, I did. The manager told me to emphasize the most important points.

1443
02:05:07,199 --> 02:05:16,000
That's great, Rose. Clear description and emphasis always make an office presentation successful.

1444
02:05:16,000 --> 02:05:21,360
Rose, do you think leadership is the most important skill in a company?

1445
02:05:21,360 --> 02:05:30,560
Yes, Nick. A good leader guides the team. Executives, seniors, and superiors must create a clear strategy.

1446
02:05:30,560 --> 02:05:39,280
I agree. Every project needs an objective and a priority. Otherwise, workers get confused.

1447
02:05:39,280 --> 02:05:47,920
True. Managers often prepare proposals, follow regulations, and remind us of our obligations and responsibilities.

1448
02:05:47,920 --> 02:05:50,960
Do you get a salary every month on time?

1449
02:05:50,960 --> 02:05:54,320
Yes, but sometimes I work extra shifts.

1450
02:05:54,320 --> 02:05:58,159
The finance department always reviews payment carefully.

1451
02:05:58,159 --> 02:06:01,920
That's good. Do you think about retirement yet?

1452
02:06:01,920 --> 02:06:09,360
Not really, but some employees register early for retirement plans. Institutions often provide insurance.

1453
02:06:09,360 --> 02:06:15,599
My uncle works in investment. He studies financial markets, stocks, and statistics.

1454
02:06:15,599 --> 02:06:23,599
That sounds serious. I know a banker who helps people with transactions like transfers and withdrawals.

1455
02:06:23,599 --> 02:06:27,760
Companies must also manage property and supplies.

1456
02:06:27,760 --> 02:06:32,800
Expanding business often requires exports and new branches.

1457
02:06:32,800 --> 02:06:40,320
Exactly. Some firms extend into international trade to grow while others retain their local market.

1458
02:06:40,320 --> 02:06:44,960
Do you think experience makes someone an expert?

1459
02:06:44,960 --> 02:06:54,880
Yes, Nick. But even experts must review, investigate, and confirm results to remain successful.

1460
02:06:54,880 --> 02:07:00,400
Rose, what is the most difficult challenge you face at work?

1461
02:07:00,400 --> 02:07:08,400
Sometimes I feel stressed when tasks affect my personal life. I must depend on my colleagues to share the load.

1462
02:07:08,400 --> 02:07:17,199
Yes, teamwork matters. A good boss can direct the crew, but if managers dismiss workers unfairly, morale drops.

1463
02:07:17,199 --> 02:07:25,280
True. Last year, my firm had to distribute staff into new divisions. It was hard to engage everyone equally.

1464
02:07:25,280 --> 02:07:30,239
I once worked in a company where the employer did not allow flexible hours.

1465
02:07:30,239 --> 02:07:33,760
It caused concern for many employees.

1466
02:07:33,760 --> 02:07:40,320
That's not acceptable. Companies should confirm new policies and explain them clearly.

1467
02:07:40,320 --> 02:07:43,040
Did you ever reject an offer?

1468
02:07:43,040 --> 02:07:49,520
Yes, I once rejected a job because the role seemed difficult and the salary was too low.

1469
02:07:49,520 --> 02:07:58,000
I understand. Every decision needs effort. Sometimes we must discover new opportunities to grow.

1470
02:07:58,000 --> 02:08:06,880
Exactly. Every discovery teaches us something. Even failure can provide experience and emphasize the need to improve.

1471
02:08:06,880 --> 02:08:17,679
You're right, Rose. In the end, challenges help us gain confidence and handle future responsibilities better.

1472
02:08:17,679 --> 02:08:28,400
Rose, yesterday, our office hosted an architecture exhibition. It was amazing to see classical designs and modern engineering models together.

1473
02:08:28,400 --> 02:08:40,560
That sounds great, Nick. I attended a similar program in July. The description was brief, but the presentation included every detail. Did they cite examples from history?

1474
02:08:40,560 --> 02:08:47,119
Yes. The chairman even cast a vote to highlight the best discovery. It was delightful.

1475
02:08:47,119 --> 02:08:53,040
Haha. Once I gave a speech and felt embarrassed because I forgot my notes.

1476
02:08:53,040 --> 02:08:56,000
Don't worry. Everybody makes mistakes.

1477
02:08:56,000 --> 02:09:01,199
Sometimes dirt on the floor or mud on shoes can be more embarrassing.

1478
02:09:01,199 --> 02:09:09,360
True. I once leaned on a wall and nearly fell. My colleague joked that I might explode with laughter.

1479
02:09:09,360 --> 02:09:16,400
That's humorous. Our team often shares jokes. It makes the atmosphere pleasant and easy.

1480
02:09:16,400 --> 02:09:21,599
Do you think competition between companies is always sensible?

1481
02:09:21,599 --> 02:09:30,800
Not always. Some competitors behave carelessly and neither side wins. Still, a fair victory is always celebrated.

1482
02:09:30,800 --> 02:09:34,719
I read an article about a revolution in farming.

1483
02:09:34,719 --> 02:09:42,480
It said even a euro or a pound invested in organic food can contribute to reducing poverty.

1484
02:09:42,480 --> 02:09:50,639
That's realistic. Environmental change affects everyone from a farmer to a princess in her palace.

1485
02:09:50,639 --> 02:09:53,679
Wow, that's a contrast.

1486
02:09:53,679 --> 02:09:58,159
Sometimes life feels like a toy in the hands of fate.

1487
02:09:58,159 --> 02:10:07,040
True, but overall personal effort matters most. Within yourself lies the spirit to pursue goals until you succeed.

1488
02:10:07,040 --> 02:10:16,960
Well said, Rose. Our ending may be different, but if we remain strong, work hard, and stay wise, the sum of our efforts will bring success.

1489
02:10:16,960 --> 02:10:27,280
Yes, Nick. Every ordinary day at work can still be brilliant if we handle it with thought, care, and humor.

1490
02:10:27,280 --> 02:10:34,239
Rose, after a long day at the office, do you prefer a hot bath or just a brief shower?

1491
02:10:34,239 --> 02:10:41,119
A bath is relaxing. Sometimes I even add cream to soften my skin. What about you?

1492
02:10:41,119 --> 02:10:46,560
I usually just take a quick shower, then eat a small bite before bed.

1493
02:10:46,560 --> 02:10:54,000
That sounds typical. Yesterday, my female colleague invited me to go dancing, but I was too tired.

1494
02:10:54,000 --> 02:11:02,239
I understand. I sometimes like to float in the pool during summer. It makes me forget the mass of problems at work.

1495
02:11:02,239 --> 02:11:08,639
That's nice. My uncle plays the organ at church. And he says music gives him energy.

1496
02:11:08,639 --> 02:11:15,440
I believe that. Once I tried skiing on a steep hill, but I fell into the sand at the bottom.

1497
02:11:15,440 --> 02:11:23,679
Haha, that's funny. I once used a tape recorder to practice English, but the wheel inside broke.

1498
02:11:23,679 --> 02:11:30,639
Technology can be silly sometimes. Do you think guns and wars still affect ordinary people?

1499
02:11:30,639 --> 02:11:40,560
Yes, Nick, sadly, but I try to focus on pleasant things. I look at the stars and yours is always the first voice I remember from our talks.

1500
02:11:40,560 --> 02:11:50,079
That's kind Rose. Life is somewhat crazy, but with patience and effort, we can still find comfort and victory.

1501
02:11:50,079 --> 02:12:06,560
Exactly. Even difficult moments can teach us to be sensible, careful, and grateful. That is the best ending for every rose. Do you like living in a big city or a small town?

1502
02:12:06,560 --> 02:12:12,400
I think a city is more exciting, but a quiet village can be peaceful, too.

1503
02:12:12,400 --> 02:12:18,000
True. In the city, every street is full of people, shops, and cars.

1504
02:12:18,000 --> 02:12:25,520
Yes. And every road leads to something new. A park, a garden, or a playground.

1505
02:12:25,520 --> 02:12:32,000
My favorite place is the square near the bridge. I often walk there in the evening.

1506
02:12:32,000 --> 02:12:39,280
That's nice. I prefer the area near the tunnel and train station. It's convenient for travel.

1507
02:12:39,280 --> 02:12:46,320
I usually take the bus from the stop near my apartment, but sometimes I go to the airport.

1508
02:12:46,320 --> 02:12:53,360
Really? I love watching planes at the airport and ships at the harbor. The port looks beautiful at night.

1509
02:12:53,360 --> 02:12:56,239
Have you seen the new tower downtown?

1510
02:12:56,239 --> 02:13:00,000
It's next to the tallest office building in the city.

1511
02:13:00,000 --> 02:13:04,960
Yes. There's also a new shop and a big store inside the mall.

1512
02:13:04,960 --> 02:13:11,599
I went to the market last weekend. The supermarket there sells fresh fruit and flowers.

1513
02:13:11,599 --> 02:13:18,400
Our city has almost everything. parks, bridges, tunnels, malls, and public transport.

1514
02:13:18,400 --> 02:13:24,639
That's why city life is so lively even though it's sometimes noisy and crowded.

1515
02:13:24,639 --> 02:13:32,719
Yes, Nick. Every city has its rhythm and it always keeps moving forward.

1516
02:13:32,719 --> 02:13:37,280
Rose, where do you usually eat when you go out in the city?

1517
02:13:37,280 --> 02:13:43,840
I like small restaurants or cafes. They are comfortable and the food is delicious.

1518
02:13:43,840 --> 02:13:49,679
I sometimes eat in a big restaurant, but I also enjoy street food near the mall.

1519
02:13:49,679 --> 02:13:56,960
That sounds fun. Last month, I stayed at a hotel near the city center. The service there was excellent.

1520
02:13:56,960 --> 02:13:58,880
Was it expensive?

1521
02:13:58,880 --> 02:14:06,000
Not really. It was cheaper than the motel I tried before. I even saw a hostel full of students.

1522
02:14:06,000 --> 02:14:13,760
When I travel, I like to visit cinemas and theaters. Watching a film or a live show helps me relax.

1523
02:14:13,760 --> 02:14:21,280
I agree. I also enjoy going to museums, art galleries, and libraries to learn new things.

1524
02:14:21,280 --> 02:14:26,719
Our city has a big stadium for sports and a concert hall for music.

1525
02:14:26,719 --> 02:14:34,320
Yes. And there is a beautiful church and a mosque near the river. The temple on the hill is also amazing.

1526
02:14:34,320 --> 02:14:36,719
I once went to a cultural event there.

1527
02:14:36,719 --> 02:14:40,800
People danced, sang, and shared traditional food.

1528
02:14:40,800 --> 02:14:52,159
That's what I love about city life, Nick. Every corner has a story. From a cafe to a theater, from a museum to a temple.

1529
02:14:52,159 --> 02:14:56,960
Rose, what city service do you think people use the most?

1530
02:14:56,960 --> 02:15:03,199
Probably the bank, Nick. Everyone needs to manage money, pay bills, or open an account.

1531
02:15:03,199 --> 02:15:11,599
True. I go to the post office often to send packages and letters. The assistants there are very friendly.

1532
02:15:11,599 --> 02:15:18,159
That's nice. I also visit the police station once in a while to renew my ID card.

1533
02:15:18,159 --> 02:15:23,920
Wow, that sounds official. Have you ever been to a fire station?

1534
02:15:23,920 --> 02:15:31,119
Yes, during an open day. The firefighters explained how they protect people and buildings.

1535
02:15:31,119 --> 02:15:38,000
That's cool. Last week, I passed by the hospital and saw a new clinic beside the pharmacy.

1536
02:15:38,000 --> 02:15:46,159
Health services are essential. We also have schools, universities, and colleges that give educational support.

1537
02:15:46,159 --> 02:15:54,079
Right. And the city court helps to keep justice. But I hope I never have to visit a prison or jail.

1538
02:15:54,079 --> 02:16:01,199
Me, too. The embassy and consulate are also important for travelers and foreign workers.

1539
02:16:01,199 --> 02:16:02,239
Yes.

1540
02:16:02,239 --> 02:16:10,079
and our community center runs free programs for families. The council supports local events and services.

1541
02:16:10,079 --> 02:16:16,960
My brother works for a government agency. He helps the public connect with different companies and factories.

1542
02:16:16,960 --> 02:16:26,239
That's great, Rose. It's amazing how many institutions work together to make a city safe and organized.

1543
02:16:26,239 --> 02:16:36,000
Rose, what do you usually do on weekends in the city? I sometimes go swimming at the sports center or I visit the gym with my friends.

1544
02:16:36,000 --> 02:16:43,679
That sounds great. I usually take my little cousin to the zoo or the aquarium. He loves animals and fish.

1545
02:16:43,679 --> 02:16:52,160
Oh, that's lovely. Last month, I took my mom to the visitor center. She wanted to see the new art exhibition there.

1546
02:16:52,160 --> 02:16:53,679
Nice.

1547
02:16:53,679 --> 02:16:59,920
I also like spending time in public areas like the park or near the parking lot at the market.

1548
02:16:59,920 --> 02:17:05,599
When I shop, I always thank the shop assistant or the cashier for their service.

1549
02:17:05,599 --> 02:17:11,840
That's polite. I also try to be patient in a queue, even when the line is long.

1550
02:17:11,840 --> 02:17:15,840
Yes, many customers forget that good service takes time.

1551
02:17:15,840 --> 02:17:20,080
Do you ever visit the public toilets or restrooms when you go out?

1552
02:17:20,080 --> 02:17:25,040
Yes, of course. They are clean and convenient in most malls.

1553
02:17:25,040 --> 02:17:31,599
Our city is really improving. The new facilities make daily life easier for everyone.

1554
02:17:31,599 --> 02:17:41,840
You're right, Nick. A good city isn't just about tall buildings. It's about comfort, care, and service for the people.

1555
02:17:41,840 --> 02:17:53,200
Rose, do you usually pay with cash or by card when you shop in the city? I mostly use my bank card, but I always keep a little cash for small things.

1556
02:17:53,200 --> 02:18:00,800
Same here. Yesterday, I went to the post office to send a parcel and I had to buy a stamp with coins.

1557
02:18:00,800 --> 02:18:03,439
Oh, yes, I remember doing that.

1558
02:18:03,439 --> 02:18:09,120
Sometimes the change is small, but it feels nice to use real money.

1559
02:18:09,120 --> 02:18:13,519
True. Do you ever pay rent or bills in person?

1560
02:18:13,519 --> 02:18:21,519
No, I usually pay online. I'd check my account, transfer the money, and get an email receipt.

1561
02:18:21,519 --> 02:18:27,920
That's smart. I once forgot to pay my phone bill, and I had to pay a late fee.

1562
02:18:27,920 --> 02:18:36,479
I hate that. Living in the city can be expensive. There are so many costs like tax, rent, and transport.

1563
02:18:36,479 --> 02:18:49,599
Yes, the price of everything keeps going up. Even a simple meal in a restaurant costs more. Now, my friend works in a bank. She helps customers apply for loans and manage their accounts.

1564
02:18:49,599 --> 02:18:55,200
That's a useful job. Good financial service keeps the city running smoothly.

1565
02:18:55,200 --> 02:19:06,240
I agree, Nick. Whether it's paying bills or buying a cup of coffee, money connects every part of city life.

1566
02:19:06,240 --> 02:19:10,399
Rose, how do you feel about living in an urban area?

1567
02:19:10,399 --> 02:19:18,080
I like it, Nick. City life is convenient, but sometimes it's also expensive and noisy.

1568
02:19:18,080 --> 02:19:26,880
That's true. I grew up in a small town, but now I enjoy the modern buildings and construction projects around us.

1569
02:19:26,880 --> 02:19:34,240
Yes, the city keeps changing. New housing estates and roads are being built every year.

1570
02:19:34,240 --> 02:19:37,439
Have you seen the new electric buses?

1571
02:19:37,439 --> 02:19:40,880
They use less fuel and help reduce pollution.

1572
02:19:40,880 --> 02:19:47,040
That's great. I think it's important for cities to invest in clean energy and good equipment.

1573
02:19:47,040 --> 02:19:53,760
Our council also started a project to improve public land and repair old fences and bridges.

1574
02:19:53,760 --> 02:19:58,000
I like that idea. It makes the city look bright and safe.

1575
02:19:58,000 --> 02:20:05,200
But the flow of traffic is still terrible. I hope the government will establish new routes soon.

1576
02:20:05,200 --> 02:20:11,520
Me, too. It's essential to plan carefully and estimate the real needs of the people.

1577
02:20:11,520 --> 02:20:20,640
Sometimes I feel the expense of city life is too high. Even simple things like rent or food cost more than before.

1578
02:20:20,640 --> 02:20:29,359
Yes, but we must admit living in an organized technical and civil environment also has its benefits.

1579
02:20:29,359 --> 02:20:38,800
That's true, Rose. The city might be busy, but it gives us access to almost everything we need.

1580
02:20:38,800 --> 02:20:44,080
Rose, cities always seem full of schools and universities.

1581
02:20:44,080 --> 02:20:47,840
Do you think education is the heart of every city?

1582
02:20:47,840 --> 02:20:54,720
Absolutely, Nick. Education encourages people to grow and ensures the future of the community.

1583
02:20:54,720 --> 02:21:02,000
That's true. In my college, we often write essays about city development and essential services.

1584
02:21:02,000 --> 02:21:10,640
Yes, I remember doing that. Our teacher asked us to establish ideas, estimate the population, and evaluate the results.

1585
02:21:10,640 --> 02:21:13,920
Did you have to find evidence for your report?

1586
02:21:13,920 --> 02:21:20,880
Of course, we had to collect data, explain our opinions, and include clear explanations.

1587
02:21:20,880 --> 02:21:23,680
Sounds just like my class.

1588
02:21:23,680 --> 02:21:30,319
We had to examine local projects and explore how urban areas improve quality of life.

1589
02:21:30,319 --> 02:21:38,000
That's interesting. My instructor always said, "Aex examples are powerful. They make learning practical."

1590
02:21:38,000 --> 02:21:44,080
I agree. Cities are full of examples that teach us how people work together.

1591
02:21:44,080 --> 02:21:55,840
Exactly. Whether through exercise, examination, or exploration, every experience helps us understand society better.

1592
02:21:55,840 --> 02:22:03,439
Rose, yesterday was Friday and the weather was incredible. Did you go anywhere in the city?

1593
02:22:03,439 --> 02:22:10,640
Yes, Nick. I went with my mom to the old district near the river. The view was bright and beautiful.

1594
02:22:10,640 --> 02:22:16,160
That's lovely. I heard they built new houses there after the flood last April.

1595
02:22:16,160 --> 02:22:22,240
Yes, the construction was massive, but everything looks clean and organized now.

1596
02:22:22,240 --> 02:22:28,960
Did you see the new fence around the park? It looks nice, though a bit dirty from the rain.

1597
02:22:28,960 --> 02:22:33,920
I did. The council hired some guys to clean it this morning. They work hard.

1598
02:22:33,920 --> 02:22:36,560
It's highly satisfying to watch.

1599
02:22:36,560 --> 02:22:44,880
You're right. Sometimes small details like a clean street or a kind guard make the city pleasant.

1600
02:22:44,880 --> 02:22:52,399
True. My daughter says she feels safe walking there. She's learning about urban life in her geography class.

1601
02:22:52,399 --> 02:22:59,760
That's wonderful. My instructor once said a city is a creation of people's minds and hearts.

1602
02:22:59,760 --> 02:23:02,960
I like that. It's a sensible thought.

1603
02:23:02,960 --> 02:23:07,760
Every person contributes something even without realizing it.

1604
02:23:07,760 --> 02:23:12,880
Do you remember that essay we wrote about pollution? The evidence was clear.

1605
02:23:12,880 --> 02:23:17,760
People must act now to prevent violence and protect the environment.

1606
02:23:17,760 --> 02:23:28,080
Yes, and we summarized the findings and explained every sequence carefully. It was a long-term project, but the results were significant.

1607
02:23:28,080 --> 02:23:37,600
I met a policeman that day. He said even small actions like recycling can make a big difference. Obviously, he's right.

1608
02:23:37,600 --> 02:23:42,960
Change doesn't happen overnight, but even a thousand small efforts matter.

1609
02:23:42,960 --> 02:23:50,880
Cities are amazing, Rose. They can be mild or noisy, rich or poor, but they always have stories.

1610
02:23:50,880 --> 02:24:05,280
Exactly, Nick. Life in the city never stops. It moves forward, teaches us lessons, and connects us all.

1611
02:24:05,280 --> 02:24:09,840
Rose, how often do you spend time with your friends?

1612
02:24:09,840 --> 02:24:18,160
Almost every weekend, Nick. Friendship means a lot to me. We meet, talk, and laugh together.

1613
02:24:18,160 --> 02:24:26,479
That's wonderful. I usually visit my neighbor and my old classmates. We drink tea, and chat about life.

1614
02:24:26,479 --> 02:24:34,000
Nice. My colleagues at work are also my friends. We share stories and help each other when things get hard.

1615
02:24:34,000 --> 02:24:36,319
That's the best kind of friendship.

1616
02:24:36,319 --> 02:24:39,359
Honest, kind, and supportive.

1617
02:24:39,359 --> 02:24:47,200
Yes. In my community, people join local events and support the elderly. It feels like a big family.

1618
02:24:47,200 --> 02:24:53,120
I like that idea. Being part of a group makes you feel you belong somewhere.

1619
02:24:53,120 --> 02:25:05,280
True. Every member of a community has a role to play. I think friendly people make a city better. A smile or small talk can change someone's mood.

1620
02:25:05,280 --> 02:25:11,120
Exactly. I try to be polite and generous with everyone, even strangers.

1621
02:25:11,120 --> 02:25:17,600
Me, too. I believe kindness is the simplest way to build real social connections.

1622
02:25:17,600 --> 02:25:26,240
You're right, Nick. Friendship and community make life warmer, happier, and more human.

1623
02:25:26,240 --> 02:25:29,520
Rose, how big is your family?

1624
02:25:29,520 --> 02:25:35,040
Pretty big, Nick. I live with my parents, my sister, and my little brother.

1625
02:25:35,040 --> 02:25:43,280
That sounds nice. I have two cousins and an uncle who live nearby. My aunt often visits us on weekends.

1626
02:25:43,280 --> 02:25:45,600
My grandparents live in the countryside.

1627
02:25:45,600 --> 02:25:51,520
My grandfather tells great stories, and my grandmother always cooks my favorite meal.

1628
02:25:51,520 --> 02:26:00,080
That's lovely. I sometimes visit my relatives during holidays. Family gatherings always make me feel calm and happy.

1629
02:26:00,080 --> 02:26:08,640
Me, too. My husband and I often take our children to visit our parents. The kids love playing with their cousins.

1630
02:26:08,640 --> 02:26:14,640
That's a good tradition. In my family, we have a small reunion every summer.

1631
02:26:14,640 --> 02:26:21,359
It must be wonderful to see everyone together, adults, teenagers, and even the little toddlers.

1632
02:26:21,359 --> 02:26:26,800
Yes, it is. Family gives us love, care, and understanding.

1633
02:26:26,800 --> 02:26:33,600
I agree. Every child learns respect and kindness from their parents and grandparents.

1634
02:26:33,600 --> 02:26:39,520
A family doesn't have to be perfect, but it should always be full of trust.

1635
02:26:39,520 --> 02:26:48,160
Exactly, Nick. Family is our first community where love begins and never ends.

1636
02:26:48,160 --> 02:26:52,960
Rose, do you enjoy going to parties and social events?

1637
02:26:52,960 --> 02:27:00,720
Yes, I love them. Last week, I went to a birthday party for my cousin, and the atmosphere was so cheerful.

1638
02:27:00,720 --> 02:27:09,280
That sounds fun. I went to a wedding last month. The couple looked amazing in their traditional costumes.

1639
02:27:09,280 --> 02:27:16,800
Oh, I love weddings. The ceremony, the music, and the dancing always make me emotional.

1640
02:27:16,800 --> 02:27:18,800
Me, too.

1641
02:27:18,800 --> 02:27:25,040
Last year, my family celebrated my parents' anniversary with a big dinner and fireworks.

1642
02:27:25,040 --> 02:27:33,600
Wow, that must have been beautiful. I once organized a picnic and a small holiday gathering for my colleagues.

1643
02:27:33,600 --> 02:27:41,760
Nice. Our office usually hosts an annual festival with music, songs, and funny performances.

1644
02:27:41,760 --> 02:27:49,200
I like community events like parades, fairs, or local exhibitions. They bring people together.

1645
02:27:49,200 --> 02:27:56,319
Yes, even small things like sharing a meal or a slice of cake make everyone feel connected.

1646
02:27:56,319 --> 02:28:11,040
When I was younger, my friends and I joined a national cultural show. We wore costumes and sang folk songs. That sounds incredible. Every celebration, big or small, creates joy and good memories.

1647
02:28:11,040 --> 02:28:19,520
Exactly, Nick. Celebrations remind us how lucky we are to share happiness with others.

1648
02:28:19,520 --> 02:28:24,160
Rose, how are you feeling today? You look really cheerful.

1649
02:28:24,160 --> 02:28:29,280
Thanks, Nick. I'm happy because I just got great news from my family.

1650
02:28:29,280 --> 02:28:35,120
That's nice. I was a bit tired this morning, but now I feel relaxed and calm.

1651
02:28:35,120 --> 02:28:37,920
Sometimes our moods change so quickly.

1652
02:28:37,920 --> 02:28:41,439
Yesterday I was upset and worried about my work.

1653
02:28:41,439 --> 02:28:47,760
I understand. I get angry when things go wrong, but I try to stay positive.

1654
02:28:47,760 --> 02:28:54,319
Me too. When I feel sad or lonely, I usually listen to music or call a friend.

1655
02:28:54,319 --> 02:29:00,960
That helps. I often go for a walk when I feel bored or stressed. It clears my mind.

1656
02:29:00,960 --> 02:29:08,479
Last week, my little sister was surprised when she won an art competition. She was proud and confident all day.

1657
02:29:08,479 --> 02:29:15,359
That's sweet. My brother gets shy in public, but he's really funny once he feels comfortable.

1658
02:29:15,359 --> 02:29:17,680
Emotions are strange, aren't they?

1659
02:29:17,680 --> 02:29:22,800
Sometimes we laugh, sometimes we cry, but that's what makes us human.

1660
02:29:22,800 --> 02:29:28,960
Exactly. Being honest about our feelings helps us understand each other better.

1661
02:29:28,960 --> 02:29:38,640
I agree, Nick. Whether we're excited, afraid, or calm, sharing emotions makes relationships stronger.

1662
02:29:38,640 --> 02:29:42,240
Rose, do you talk to your friends every day?

1663
02:29:42,240 --> 02:29:47,280
Not every day, Nick, but I try to call or text them a few times a week.

1664
02:29:47,280 --> 02:29:59,760
That's nice. I usually send short messages or emails when I'm busy at work. Sometimes I just like to chat face to face. I think real conversation feels more personal.

1665
02:29:59,760 --> 02:30:08,160
I agree. Listening is just as important as speaking. Good communication keeps friendships strong.

1666
02:30:08,160 --> 02:30:17,200
Yes. My cousin and I always share ideas and discuss things honestly. Even when we disagree, we respect each other's opinions.

1667
02:30:17,200 --> 02:30:24,000
That's how it should be. Arguments happen, but we should never fight just to win.

1668
02:30:24,000 --> 02:30:29,840
True. When I hurt someone's feelings, I always apologize and try to make peace.

1669
02:30:29,840 --> 02:30:35,760
That's thoughtful. I also thank people when they help me or support me.

1670
02:30:35,760 --> 02:30:38,319
Gratitude means a lot.

1671
02:30:38,319 --> 02:30:44,800
My mom says, "If you make a mistake, say sorry. If you're wrong, forgive."

1672
02:30:44,800 --> 02:30:53,120
Wise words. Communication is more than words. It's about kindness, understanding, and trust.

1673
02:30:53,120 --> 02:31:03,120
Exactly, Nick. When people express their feelings openly and listen carefully, every relationship grows stronger.

1674
02:31:03,120 --> 02:31:07,040
Rose, do you believe in love at first sight?

1675
02:31:07,040 --> 02:31:14,080
Uh-huh. I'm not sure, Nick. I think real love grows slowly with trust and respect.

1676
02:31:14,080 --> 02:31:21,439
That's true. My parents have been married for 20 years and their relationship still feels strong.

1677
02:31:21,439 --> 02:31:29,760
That's beautiful. My husband and I have learned that marriage is not always easy. It takes patience and care.

1678
02:31:29,760 --> 02:31:36,640
I can imagine. Every couple faces problems, but communication helps them stay together.

1679
02:31:36,640 --> 02:31:42,240
Yes. When my partner and I argue, we try to listen and forgive each other.

1680
02:31:42,240 --> 02:31:50,160
That's wise. My friend had an argument with his girlfriend, but they decided to talk calmly instead of fighting.

1681
02:31:50,160 --> 02:31:57,439
Sometimes people expect love to be perfect, but even small disagreements can make us understand each other better.

1682
02:31:57,439 --> 02:32:00,960
Right. Love is not just about romance.

1683
02:32:00,960 --> 02:32:04,479
It's also about support and kindness.

1684
02:32:04,479 --> 02:32:11,840
Exactly. When you love someone, you depend on them, but you also help them become independent.

1685
02:32:11,840 --> 02:32:14,800
That's a wonderful balance.

1686
02:32:14,800 --> 02:32:31,520
I think being honest and caring is more important than being perfect. I agree, Nick. Whether it's a date, a marriage, or simple friendship, love is the heart of every human connection.

1687
02:32:31,520 --> 02:32:36,960
Rose, do you think people are born kind or do they learn to be kind?

1688
02:32:36,960 --> 02:32:43,040
That's an interesting question, Nick. I think kindness comes from experience and understanding.

1689
02:32:43,040 --> 02:32:51,200
I agree. My grandfather always said, "Character is what you do when no one is watching."

1690
02:32:51,200 --> 02:32:59,280
That's true. I really admire honest and confident people. Their attitude inspires others.

1691
02:32:59,280 --> 02:33:15,280
Yes, confidence is attractive. But some people are shy or nervous in public even though they're nice inside. I know my colleague is very independent and serious at work, but at home she is funny and relaxed.

1692
02:33:15,280 --> 02:33:18,720
I like people who show their real personality.

1693
02:33:18,720 --> 02:33:22,160
Being natural makes relationships easier.

1694
02:33:22,160 --> 02:33:28,240
Absolutely. We should also be aware of how our behavior influences others.

1695
02:33:28,240 --> 02:33:34,240
I try to stay positive and polite even when I disagree with someone's opinion.

1696
02:33:34,240 --> 02:33:40,240
Me too. A friendly attitude can change a negative situation into something peaceful.

1697
02:33:40,240 --> 02:33:46,319
It's amazing how one's smile or kind word can transform someone's day.

1698
02:33:46,319 --> 02:33:55,280
Yes, Nick. Our personality, kindness, and understanding are what make us truly human.

1699
02:33:55,280 --> 02:34:01,439
Rose, how was your weekend? Did you do anything special on Saturday or Sunday?

1700
02:34:01,439 --> 02:34:09,680
Yes, Nick. On Saturday, I helped my mom organize a charity event in our district. It was small but meaningful.

1701
02:34:09,680 --> 02:34:17,120
That's lovely. I spent Sunday morning teaching music to children. One boy played an instrument beautifully.

1702
02:34:17,120 --> 02:34:25,040
Oh, that's wonderful. I lent my old guitar to a teenager who couldn't afford one. He was incredibly thankful.

1703
02:34:25,040 --> 02:34:32,960
You're so generous, Rose. I sometimes volunteer, too. Last month, I joined a group cleaning a park after a flood.

1704
02:34:32,960 --> 02:34:38,560
I admire that. Small actions show how powerful kindness can be.

1705
02:34:38,560 --> 02:34:44,080
Do you believe in ghosts? My cousin swears he saw one in an old building.

1706
02:34:44,080 --> 02:34:51,520
Haha, maybe just his imagination. I'd rather believe in love stories, not scary ones.

1707
02:34:51,520 --> 02:35:05,040
Fair enough. My grandmother used to tell tales about kings and queens when I was a child. Those stories always had deep lessons about life, courage, and the human soul.

1708
02:35:05,040 --> 02:35:14,720
True. I occasionally wonder how people in the past survived difficult times without phones, cars, or even fridges.

1709
02:35:14,720 --> 02:35:22,560
Yes, life was simpler but harder. Still, every decade leaves its own beauty and memories.

1710
02:35:22,560 --> 02:35:30,479
You're right. Even though the world can be ugly or unfair sometimes, we must focus on the positive.

1711
02:35:30,479 --> 02:35:36,080
Exactly. Every person, no matter how small, can make a significant difference.

1712
02:35:36,080 --> 02:35:40,399
That's such a reasonable and hopeful way to see life.

1713
02:35:40,399 --> 02:35:50,960
Thanks, Nick. Whether it's Saturday joy or Monday stress, every moment teaches us something valuable about being human.

1714
02:35:50,960 --> 02:35:54,960
Rose, have you finished packing for your trip abroad yet?

1715
02:35:54,960 --> 02:36:02,399
Almost, Nick, I've already booked my flight and hotel. Now I just need to check my passport and visa.

1716
02:36:02,399 --> 02:36:09,520
Good idea. I always keep my passport, ID card, and travel documents in one small folder.

1717
02:36:09,520 --> 02:36:16,399
Same here. I also printed my ticket and boarding pass. It helps me check in faster at the airport.

1718
02:36:16,399 --> 02:36:18,880
Don't forget to bring some cash.

1719
02:36:18,880 --> 02:36:21,600
Sometimes the card machine doesn't work.

1720
02:36:21,600 --> 02:36:28,319
Yes, I'll take my wallet and purse just in case. I'm also carrying my credit card for safety.

1721
02:36:28,319 --> 02:36:31,280
How much luggage are you bringing?

1722
02:36:31,280 --> 02:36:37,760
Only one suitcase and a backpack. I don't like waiting too long at baggage claim.

1723
02:36:37,760 --> 02:36:45,040
That's smart. I once had to stand in a long queue at customs just to find my bag.

1724
02:36:45,040 --> 02:36:52,319
Oh, no. I always fill in the customs form carefully and keep a copy with my identification.

1725
02:36:52,319 --> 02:36:57,359
That's important. Make sure your name and stamp are clear before you leave.

1726
02:36:57,359 --> 02:36:59,760
Thanks, Nick. Everything's ready.

1727
02:36:59,760 --> 02:37:08,319
Documents, money, and luggage. Now, I just need to relax and enjoy the trip.

1728
02:37:08,319 --> 02:37:18,479
Rose, how early do you usually arrive at the airport before a flight? I try to arrive at least 2 hours before departure just in case of a delay.

1729
02:37:18,479 --> 02:37:24,479
That's smart. I once missed my flight because I didn't check the timet carefully.

1730
02:37:24,479 --> 02:37:31,359
Oh no. I always keep my schedule on my phone. It helps me track the departure gate and terminal.

1731
02:37:31,359 --> 02:37:33,920
Have you gone through security yet?

1732
02:37:33,920 --> 02:37:47,439
Yes, it was smooth this time. The officers checked my luggage, but everything was fine. I hate waiting at customs. The line is always long and people forget their boarding passes.

1733
02:37:47,439 --> 02:37:53,120
I know. The last time I flew, I had to run to the gate because of a security check.

1734
02:37:53,120 --> 02:37:58,160
That's stressful. Do you prefer the window seat or the aisle seat?

1735
02:37:58,160 --> 02:38:04,800
The window, of course. I love watching the airplane take off and seeing the clouds below.

1736
02:38:04,800 --> 02:38:10,720
Me, too. Don't forget to fasten your seat belt before the plane starts moving.

1737
02:38:10,720 --> 02:38:20,160
I won't. I am just excited to begin my journey. Every flight feels like a new adventure.

1738
02:38:20,160 --> 02:38:24,319
Rose, where are you planning to travel this holiday?

1739
02:38:24,319 --> 02:38:31,359
I'm going on a trip to Japan. I've always wanted to explore Tokyo and visit famous attractions.

1740
02:38:31,359 --> 02:38:34,479
That's exciting. I went there last year.

1741
02:38:34,479 --> 02:38:39,280
The food was delicious and every street felt alive.

1742
02:38:39,280 --> 02:38:46,000
I can't wait. I already bought a guide book and a map and I downloaded some brochures about sightseeing tours.

1743
02:38:46,000 --> 02:38:51,680
Smart move. Are you joining a tour group or traveling independently?

1744
02:38:51,680 --> 02:38:57,600
I'll join a small tour at first, but later I want to travel alone and meet local people.

1745
02:38:57,600 --> 02:39:10,240
That sounds perfect. Don't forget to take photos. They'll make great memories. Of course, I love taking pictures of landmarks and natural attractions like mountains and rivers.

1746
02:39:10,240 --> 02:39:13,040
Do you enjoy adventure travel?

1747
02:39:13,040 --> 02:39:20,399
Yes, I do. Last summer, I joined an excursion to a mountain village. It was peaceful and beautiful.

1748
02:39:20,399 --> 02:39:28,479
Nice. When I travel, I always plan my journey carefully and keep extra information like emergency numbers.

1749
02:39:28,479 --> 02:39:37,200
That's a good habit, Nick. Traveling helps us explore the world and learn from every experience.

1750
02:39:37,200 --> 02:39:40,720
Rose, where are you staying during your trip?

1751
02:39:40,720 --> 02:39:47,040
I booked a small hotel in the city center. It's close to the main attractions and the train station.

1752
02:39:47,040 --> 02:39:54,399
That's convenient. I usually stay in motel when I travel by car. They're simple but comfortable.

1753
02:39:54,399 --> 02:40:00,640
I tried a hostel once. It was cheap and full of friendly tourists from different countries.

1754
02:40:00,640 --> 02:40:08,720
That sounds fun. I once stayed in a cozy guest house near the beach. The owner was very kind.

1755
02:40:08,720 --> 02:40:16,720
Oh, I love places like that. Last year, I stayed at a mountain resort. The view was amazing.

1756
02:40:16,720 --> 02:40:19,200
Have you ever tried camping?

1757
02:40:19,200 --> 02:40:26,960
Yes, I went to a campsite in the countryside. The facilities were clean and we even had small cabins to sleep in.

1758
02:40:26,960 --> 02:40:35,600
That sounds great. I prefer hotels with good service, but sometimes nature feels more peaceful.

1759
02:40:35,600 --> 02:40:47,600
I agree, Nick. No matter where you stay, a hostel, hotel, or resort, comfort and kindness make the best memories.

1760
02:40:47,600 --> 02:40:52,560
Rose, what kind of places do you like to visit when you travel?

1761
02:40:52,560 --> 02:40:58,960
I really love nature, Nick. Beaches, mountains, and forests make me feel peaceful.

1762
02:40:58,960 --> 02:41:06,319
Me, too. I remember climbing a hill in the countryside and watching the sunset over the river.

1763
02:41:06,319 --> 02:41:13,840
That sounds amazing. I once took a boat across a lake and saw the reflection of the mountains in the water.

1764
02:41:13,840 --> 02:41:20,880
I'd love that. My dream destination is an island with white sand and blue ocean waves.

1765
02:41:20,880 --> 02:41:30,240
That's perfect. I also want to visit a desert one day. The wide open space looks both quiet and powerful.

1766
02:41:30,240 --> 02:41:38,240
Deserts can be beautiful, but my favorite trip was hiking through a jungle. The air felt fresh and alive.

1767
02:41:38,240 --> 02:41:40,800
Wow, that must have been exciting.

1768
02:41:40,800 --> 02:41:51,439
Nature always shows us how beautiful the world is. I agree. Every landscape from a green hill to a deep forest has its own magic.

1769
02:41:51,439 --> 02:42:00,800
Yes, Nick. Wherever we go, nature reminds us to slow down and appreciate every moment.

1770
02:42:00,800 --> 02:42:07,520
Rose, when you travel, do you like visiting historic places or modern attractions?

1771
02:42:07,520 --> 02:42:15,600
I enjoy both, Nick. I love exploring museums and old monuments because they tell stories about the past.

1772
02:42:15,600 --> 02:42:22,000
I agree. When I visited Paris, the art galleries and palaces were incredible.

1773
02:42:22,000 --> 02:42:24,720
Every painting felt alive.

1774
02:42:24,720 --> 02:42:32,399
That sounds beautiful. I once went to an ancient castle in Scotland. It looked straight out of a fairy tale.

1775
02:42:32,399 --> 02:42:40,080
Wow. I've always wanted to see a real castle. My favorite was a marble temple in Thailand.

1776
02:42:40,080 --> 02:42:50,240
Oh yes, temples are amazing. I also visited a church in Italy and a mosque in Istanbul. Each place had its own spirit.

1777
02:42:50,240 --> 02:42:57,359
That's so true. The architecture of those buildings is breathtaking. Every stone has history.

1778
02:42:57,359 --> 02:43:06,319
I love how different cultures express beauty. Visiting an exhibition or a concert helps me understand people better.

1779
02:43:06,319 --> 02:43:26,399
I also enjoy theater shows and festivals. They make the city feel alive with music, dance, and laughter. Yes, Nick. Whether it's a museum, a palace, or a local performance, every cultural experience becomes a lasting memory.

1780
02:43:26,399 --> 02:43:31,439
Rose, what do you think traveling abroad teaches people the most?

1781
02:43:31,439 --> 02:43:37,280
I think it teaches independence. Nick, when you travel, you have to make your own decisions.

1782
02:43:37,280 --> 02:43:45,359
That's true. Every trip gives you new information and new perspectives. You learn how different cultures live.

1783
02:43:45,359 --> 02:43:53,279
Yes. And it helps you understand yourself better, too. Traveling improves confidence and communication.

1784
02:43:53,279 --> 02:44:00,720
I agree. I used to be shy, but now I feel more independent and open-minded after traveling alone.

1785
02:44:00,720 --> 02:44:02,880
That's a great improvement.

1786
02:44:02,880 --> 02:44:08,160
I always imagine myself exploring the world as a student of life.

1787
02:44:08,160 --> 02:44:17,520
Nicely said. When I travel, I like to inform myself first. Reading a guide book or checking facts online.

1788
02:44:17,520 --> 02:44:24,880
Same here. I love to identify interesting places and include local activities in my plan.

1789
02:44:24,880 --> 02:44:39,439
It's amazing how travel increases your knowledge and influences how you see people. Exactly. Every journey feels like a classroom full of lessons, challenges, and discoveries.

1790
02:44:39,439 --> 02:44:49,840
I couldn't agree more, Rose. Travel isn't just about movement. It's about growth and understanding.

1791
02:44:49,840 --> 02:44:56,000
Rose, what's the most unforgettable travel experience you've ever had?

1792
02:44:56,000 --> 02:45:05,520
Oh, that's hard to choose, Nick, but I'd say my trip last September was amazing, even though a hurricane almost ruined it.

1793
02:45:05,520 --> 02:45:07,279
A hurricane?

1794
02:45:07,279 --> 02:45:10,880
That sounds frightening. What happened?

1795
02:45:10,880 --> 02:45:18,560
Luckily, it passed quickly. The local people were so gentle and helpful. I was impressed by their kindness.

1796
02:45:18,560 --> 02:45:23,840
That's wonderful. I once met a famous celebrity at an airport in October.

1797
02:45:23,840 --> 02:45:25,760
Totally by surprise.

1798
02:45:25,760 --> 02:45:29,920
Really? That's incredible. Did you talk to them?

1799
02:45:29,920 --> 02:45:37,760
Just a few words. They smiled, signed my ticket, and said, "Travel safely wherever you go."

1800
02:45:37,760 --> 02:45:46,720
That's nice. I always remind myself to travel with purpose, not just for photos. Every journey deserves meaning.

1801
02:45:46,720 --> 02:45:56,720
Indeed. I like to observe things closely. The shapes of buildings, the color of wood, even the silence of old temples.

1802
02:45:56,720 --> 02:46:01,520
You sound like a writer, Nick. You could publish a travel edition one day.

1803
02:46:01,520 --> 02:46:05,840
Haha, maybe. I enjoy recalling details.

1804
02:46:05,840 --> 02:46:11,359
The pace of city life, the mirror-like lakes, and the sound of laughter.

1805
02:46:11,359 --> 02:46:18,960
My favorite moment was in June, walking through a forest path. The air was cool and the light soft and brown.

1806
02:46:18,960 --> 02:46:28,000
That sounds peaceful. Sometimes we forget how vital nature is until we step away from our busy schedules.

1807
02:46:28,000 --> 02:46:37,120
Yes. Traveling helps us practice patience, see things from a new perspective and appreciate beauty everywhere.

1808
02:46:37,120 --> 02:46:50,640
Exactly, Rose. Every trip, whether short or long, transforms us. The world is wide and wonder never ends.

1809
02:46:50,640 --> 02:46:56,560
Rose, what's your favorite meal of the day? Breakfast, lunch, or dinner?

1810
02:46:56,560 --> 02:47:02,560
I'd say breakfast, Nick. I love starting my day with warm tea and fresh bread.

1811
02:47:02,560 --> 02:47:09,040
That sounds nice. I usually skip breakfast and just have a quick snack before work.

1812
02:47:09,040 --> 02:47:15,359
You should eat more in the morning. A good breakfast gives you energy for the whole day.

1813
02:47:15,359 --> 02:47:21,680
True. I normally have lunch with my colleagues. We sit at the same table every afternoon.

1814
02:47:21,680 --> 02:47:29,040
I do that too. I always bring my own bowl and spoon, but sometimes I eat at the cafe nearby.

1815
02:47:29,040 --> 02:47:31,520
Do you cook dinner at home?

1816
02:47:31,520 --> 02:47:37,920
Yes, I do. I usually set the table with plates, forks, knives, and napkins.

1817
02:47:37,920 --> 02:47:44,960
That sounds lovely. I like to use a tablecloth on weekends. It makes the meal feel special.

1818
02:47:44,960 --> 02:47:51,279
Oh, that's a nice habit. Do you use chopsticks or a fork when you eat noodles?

1819
02:47:51,279 --> 02:47:57,359
I prefer chopsticks, but when I eat steak, I use a fork and knife like a gentleman.

1820
02:47:57,359 --> 02:48:08,240
Haha, that's polite of you, Nick. No matter how we eat with a spoon, fork, or chopsticks, sharing a meal always feels good.

1821
02:48:08,240 --> 02:48:14,399
Rose, this restaurant looks amazing. Did you make a reservation?

1822
02:48:14,399 --> 02:48:20,880
Yes, I booked a table yesterday. The waiter said tonight's buffet is very popular.

1823
02:48:20,880 --> 02:48:24,960
Great choice. I love trying new dishes.

1824
02:48:24,960 --> 02:48:27,439
Let's look at the menu.

1825
02:48:27,439 --> 02:48:29,680
Everything sounds delicious.

1826
02:48:29,680 --> 02:48:37,520
I agree. For the starter, I'll order soup. And for the main course, maybe grilled chicken with vegetables.

1827
02:48:37,520 --> 02:48:44,399
That sounds tasty. I think I'll try the seafood pasta. I've heard the chef here is famous.

1828
02:48:44,399 --> 02:48:51,359
Oh, yes. He's a great cook. He trained in Italy and always prepares food with fresh ingredients.

1829
02:48:51,359 --> 02:48:55,439
Should we get drinks? I'll have a glass of wine.

1830
02:48:55,439 --> 02:48:57,600
I'll just take some water. Thank you.

1831
02:48:57,600 --> 02:49:00,080
I'm still full from lunch.

1832
02:49:00,080 --> 02:49:06,479
No problem. The service here is excellent. The waiter is polite and quick.

1833
02:49:06,479 --> 02:49:11,920
Yes. And the waitress smiled when we walked in. That's always a good sign.

1834
02:49:11,920 --> 02:49:18,080
True. After dinner, don't forget to ask for the bill. I'll leave a nice tip for them.

1835
02:49:18,080 --> 02:49:27,600
That's kind of you, Nick. Eating out is always fun. Good food, good company, and great service.

1836
02:49:27,600 --> 02:49:31,200
Rose, what kind of food do you like the most?

1837
02:49:31,200 --> 02:49:36,560
I love Asian food, Nick. Especially rice, noodles, and spicy soup.

1838
02:49:36,560 --> 02:49:43,359
Sounds delicious. I often eat pasta with tomato sauce or baked potatoes with cheese.

1839
02:49:43,359 --> 02:49:50,399
Oh, I love potatoes, too. They taste great, boiled, fried, or even mashed with butter.

1840
02:49:50,399 --> 02:49:53,439
What about vegetables?

1841
02:49:53,439 --> 02:50:01,040
I usually cook carrots, onions, and lettuce. Sometimes I add beans, peas, or corn for extra flavor.

1842
02:50:01,040 --> 02:50:04,240
That's healthy. I try to eat more fruit.

1843
02:50:04,240 --> 02:50:07,840
Apples, bananas, and oranges are my favorites.

1844
02:50:07,840 --> 02:50:16,000
I also enjoy grapes, strawberries, and cherries. In summer, I love fresh melon and pineapple.

1845
02:50:16,000 --> 02:50:19,200
Yum. What about meat?

1846
02:50:19,200 --> 02:50:26,240
I don't eat much, but sometimes I have chicken or fish. My husband loves beef and seafood.

1847
02:50:26,240 --> 02:50:37,840
I like lamb when it's grilled. The smell is amazing. Oh, and I can't forget eggs and milk. I use butter, yogurt, and a bit of sugar when I bake.

1848
02:50:37,840 --> 02:50:45,359
That sounds perfect. A balanced meal always includes meat, vegetables, and fruit.

1849
02:50:45,359 --> 02:50:54,399
Exactly, Nick. Good food makes people happy. It's the best part of every day.

1850
02:50:54,399 --> 02:51:05,760
Rose, do you like cooking at home or eating out? I prefer cooking at home, Nick. It's relaxing and I can try new recipes in my kitchen.

1851
02:51:05,760 --> 02:51:09,520
That's great. What kind of dishes do you usually make?

1852
02:51:09,520 --> 02:51:12,000
I love to bake cakes and cookies.

1853
02:51:12,000 --> 02:51:16,319
Sometimes I boil noodles or fry vegetables with garlic and oil.

1854
02:51:16,319 --> 02:51:21,120
That sounds tasty. I often roast chicken or grill fish for dinner.

1855
02:51:21,120 --> 02:51:23,760
I tried steaming dumplings last week.

1856
02:51:23,760 --> 02:51:25,920
They turned out delicious.

1857
02:51:25,920 --> 02:51:29,840
Wow. I've never made dumplings before.

1858
02:51:29,840 --> 02:51:32,399
Do you mix the filling yourself?

1859
02:51:32,399 --> 02:51:40,319
Yes, I chop the vegetables, slice some meat, and stir everything together. Then I pour a bit of soy sauce on top.

1860
02:51:40,319 --> 02:51:46,720
Sounds perfect. I like the smell of food when it's cooking. It fills the whole house.

1861
02:51:46,720 --> 02:51:49,760
Me, too. I always keep my kitchen clean.

1862
02:51:49,760 --> 02:51:57,600
I wash the plates, put the spoons and forks back into the cupboard, and wipe the table. You're very organized, Rose.

1863
02:51:57,600 --> 02:52:02,560
I usually forget something, like turning off the cooker.

1864
02:52:02,560 --> 02:52:14,080
Haha, that's funny, Nick. Cooking isn't just about food. It's about patience, love, and little mistakes that make big memories.

1865
02:52:14,080 --> 02:52:26,560
Rose, what kind of flavors do you enjoy the most? I like spicy and sweet food, Nick. But sometimes I enjoy something sour like lemon juice or pickles.

1866
02:52:26,560 --> 02:52:30,319
Interesting. I prefer mild flavors.

1867
02:52:30,319 --> 02:52:32,800
Nothing too salty or bitter.

1868
02:52:32,800 --> 02:52:38,399
Oh, really? I once tried a dish so spicy that I almost cried.

1869
02:52:38,399 --> 02:52:45,920
Haha, that happens to me, too. I like fresh ingredients. They make everything taste better.

1870
02:52:45,920 --> 02:52:53,600
Yes, I always use fresh fruit and vegetables. Frozen food is fine, but it never tastes the same.

1871
02:52:53,600 --> 02:53:00,800
True. My favorite comfort food is hot soup on a cold day. It feels warm and peaceful.

1872
02:53:00,800 --> 02:53:07,680
That sounds nice. I love ice cream when the weather is hot. Sweet food always makes me smile.

1873
02:53:07,680 --> 02:53:13,760
Food can change your mood, right? A delicious meal can make a bad day feel better.

1874
02:53:13,760 --> 02:53:21,760
Exactly. When my family celebrates a birthday or festival, we cook together and enjoy a big feast.

1875
02:53:21,760 --> 02:53:28,800
I like that. Cooking together creates memories, laughter, and love around the table.

1876
02:53:28,800 --> 02:53:32,319
Yes, Nick. Food isn't just about flavor.

1877
02:53:32,319 --> 02:53:38,720
It's about feelings, happiness, and sharing life with others.

1878
02:53:38,720 --> 02:53:42,960
Rose, what inspired you to start cooking?

1879
02:53:42,960 --> 02:53:50,319
Honestly, Nick, I used to watch cooking shows on TV. The chef's skills and passion always inspired me.

1880
02:53:50,319 --> 02:53:58,560
I know that feeling. I once watched an interview with a famous cook who said, "Cooking is a language of love."

1881
02:53:58,560 --> 02:54:07,439
That's beautiful. I believe every dish has a story. Following the right instructions can turn simple ingredients into art.

1882
02:54:07,439 --> 02:54:14,080
True. I sometimes attend food lectures or cooking sessions to learn new techniques.

1883
02:54:14,080 --> 02:54:20,240
Oh, I'd love that. My cousin studies nutrition and teaches people how to cook healthy meals.

1884
02:54:20,240 --> 02:54:25,439
That's amazing. Do you ever judge cooking competitions?

1885
02:54:25,439 --> 02:54:32,319
No, but I enjoy watching them. The atmosphere is full of excitement and creative ideas.

1886
02:54:32,319 --> 02:54:41,359
Cooking really involves intelligence and intention. You need to plan, focus, and think about every detail.

1887
02:54:41,359 --> 02:54:47,920
Exactly. I always tell my students that improvement comes from patience and practice.

1888
02:54:47,920 --> 02:54:56,399
Wise words. Cooking isn't only about taste. It's about learning, sharing, and understanding people through food.

1889
02:54:56,399 --> 02:55:04,960
Well said, Nick. Every meal we make is a lesson in culture, language, and love.

1890
02:55:04,960 --> 02:55:08,560
Rose, do you ever make a mess in the kitchen?

1891
02:55:08,560 --> 02:55:15,200
Haha, all the time, Nick. Yesterday, I burned the toast and nearly set off the smoke alarm.

1892
02:55:15,200 --> 02:55:22,000
Oh, no. I once dropped a whole pan of soup. My floor looked like a tomato storm.

1893
02:55:22,000 --> 02:55:38,000
That's funny. I usually clean quietly after cooking. I grab a cloth, brush off crumbs, and put dishes back in the cupboard. You're much more organized than me. I often forget where I left my cooker lid or knife.

1894
02:55:38,000 --> 02:55:46,160
I keep everything in order. Folding napkins, washing plates, removing stains. It's almost like a routine.

1895
02:55:46,160 --> 02:55:53,600
You sound like a professional chef. Do you use wooden spoons or metal ones?

1896
02:55:53,600 --> 02:55:59,439
Wooden ones always. They feel safer and don't scratch the pans.

1897
02:55:59,439 --> 02:56:06,479
Good choice. I once bought a sharp new knife and cut myself slightly. I was so frightened.

1898
02:56:06,479 --> 02:56:13,200
Ouch, that sounds painful. I hope you cleaned it with warm water and used a plaster.

1899
02:56:13,200 --> 02:56:19,680
I did. Cooking has taught me patience and to never hurry when using sharp tools.

1900
02:56:19,680 --> 02:56:29,680
Exactly, Nick. Every kitchen mistake, from a burnt pan to a lost spoon, teaches us something useful.

1901
02:56:29,680 --> 02:56:34,720
Rose, do you have a favorite food memory from your childhood?

1902
02:56:34,720 --> 02:56:43,439
Yes, Nick, when I was a teenage girl, my mom and I used to bake cakes every Sunday. The smell filled the whole house.

1903
02:56:43,439 --> 02:56:49,920
That sounds lovely. My grandfather was a fisherman, so we always had fresh fish.

1904
02:56:49,920 --> 02:56:53,680
He taught me how to clean it carefully before cooking.

1905
02:56:53,680 --> 02:57:03,279
That's a wonderful tradition. I once joined a fishing trip with my uncle. We caught different species of fish and cooked them right beside the river.

1906
02:57:03,279 --> 02:57:11,520
What a great experience. I once met a kind gentleman at a local fair who taught me how to make honey from bees.

1907
02:57:11,520 --> 02:57:21,840
Wow, that's so interesting. Nature always surprises us. From bees making honey to storms that change the soil for farming.

1908
02:57:21,840 --> 02:57:29,279
True. Food connects us to nature and history. Every recipe has its origin and story.

1909
02:57:29,279 --> 02:57:37,279
Yes, some traditional dishes are hundreds of years old. They carry culture, love, and family memories.

1910
02:57:37,279 --> 02:57:41,279
I believe cooking is like storytelling.

1911
02:57:41,279 --> 02:57:45,600
It reminds us of people we miss and moments we cherish.

1912
02:57:45,600 --> 02:57:51,279
Exactly. Food can heal sadness and bring joy even on the darkest day.

1913
02:57:51,279 --> 02:57:58,640
You're right, Rose. Whether it's a simple meal or a great feast, sharing food brings peace to the soul.

1914
02:57:58,640 --> 02:58:07,920
Beautifully said, Rose, do you usually shop at the supermarket or small local stores?

1915
02:58:07,920 --> 02:58:13,520
I go to the supermarket for groceries, but I like boutiques for clothes.

1916
02:58:13,520 --> 02:58:20,399
Same here. Big stores have more products, but small shops feel more personal.

1917
02:58:20,399 --> 02:58:25,520
Yes. The shopkeeper often remembers you and offers help politely.

1918
02:58:25,520 --> 02:58:29,920
Look at this shelf. The quality of these items looks quite good.

1919
02:58:29,920 --> 02:58:35,680
I agree. This brand is popular and the price seems reasonable today.

1920
02:58:35,680 --> 02:58:40,399
There's a discount sign. It says 20% off all clothing.

1921
02:58:40,399 --> 02:58:44,640
That's a great deal. I might buy a shirt and a pair of trousers.

1922
02:58:44,640 --> 02:58:47,520
Are you paying with cash or card?

1923
02:58:47,520 --> 02:58:52,000
I'll use my debit card. I don't carry much cash in my wallet anymore.

1924
02:58:52,000 --> 02:58:56,240
The cashier looks busy. There's a long queue at the counter.

1925
02:58:56,240 --> 02:59:02,720
That's okay. We can wait. Shopping always takes time, especially on weekends.

1926
02:59:02,720 --> 02:59:07,520
True. I like checking the bill carefully before I pay.

1927
02:59:07,520 --> 02:59:13,760
Me, too. It helps me control my budget and avoid extra spending.

1928
02:59:13,760 --> 02:59:20,560
Shopping is more enjoyable when you buy what you really need.

1929
02:59:20,560 --> 02:59:33,120
Rose, this clothing store has many styles. Do you like modern fashion? I do, Nick, but I prefer simple clothes that are comfortable and easy to wear.

1930
02:59:33,120 --> 02:59:39,439
That makes sense. This jacket looks stylish and the material feels warm.

1931
02:59:39,439 --> 02:59:45,680
Yes, it's wool. Wool coats are great in winter, but silk feels nicer in summer.

1932
02:59:45,680 --> 02:59:49,920
I'm thinking about buying jeans and a sweater for work.

1933
02:59:49,920 --> 02:59:55,200
Good idea. You should try them on first to check the size and fit.

1934
02:59:55,200 --> 03:00:00,800
You're right. I don't want to buy something uncomfortable or too tight.

1935
03:00:00,800 --> 03:00:06,319
Look at this dress. The color is unusual, but it suits you well.

1936
03:00:06,319 --> 03:00:10,399
Really, I'm not used to wearing bright colors like this.

1937
03:00:10,399 --> 03:00:15,680
You'll get used to it. Fashion is about confidence and personal style.

1938
03:00:15,680 --> 03:00:19,200
Should I choose this one or the darker jacket?

1939
03:00:19,200 --> 03:00:23,920
I pick the darker one. It matches more clothes and looks professional.

1940
03:00:23,920 --> 03:00:28,080
Okay, I'll take your advice and wear it to the office.

1941
03:00:28,080 --> 03:00:33,120
Great choice. You can return or exchange it if it doesn't feel right.

1942
03:00:33,120 --> 03:00:35,040
Thanks, Rose.

1943
03:00:35,040 --> 03:00:41,120
Shopping is easier when someone helps you decide.

1944
03:00:41,120 --> 03:00:44,479
Rose, how do you usually pay for things?

1945
03:00:44,479 --> 03:00:46,560
Cash or card?

1946
03:00:46,560 --> 03:00:52,000
I mostly pay by card now. It's faster and easier to track my spending.

1947
03:00:52,000 --> 03:00:56,800
I agree. I only keep some coins and notes for small purchases.

1948
03:00:56,800 --> 03:01:02,240
Same here. I also check my bank account often to manage my budget.

1949
03:01:02,240 --> 03:01:04,640
Do you ever use credit cards?

1950
03:01:04,640 --> 03:01:11,200
Yes, but carefully. Credit is useful, but interest can become a problem.

1951
03:01:11,200 --> 03:01:16,560
That's true. I don't like owing money or paying extra fees.

1952
03:01:16,560 --> 03:01:21,439
Me neither. I prefer to save money instead of borrowing it.

1953
03:01:21,439 --> 03:01:26,000
Sometimes people spend without thinking and end up in debt.

1954
03:01:26,000 --> 03:01:31,120
Exactly. Planning your expenses helps you avoid financial stress.

1955
03:01:31,120 --> 03:01:34,640
I always review the bill before making a payment.

1956
03:01:34,640 --> 03:01:39,439
That's a good habit. It helps prevent mistakes or extra charges.

1957
03:01:39,439 --> 03:01:42,399
Do you use ATMs often?

1958
03:01:42,399 --> 03:01:46,800
Occasionally. I withdraw cash only when I really need it.

1959
03:01:46,800 --> 03:01:53,040
Being careful with money gives you more freedom in the long run.

1960
03:01:53,040 --> 03:01:58,960
Rose, this store is having a big sale today. Did you see the signs?

1961
03:01:58,960 --> 03:02:10,160
Yes, Nick. They're offering discounts on shoes, jackets, and accessories. I like sales, but only when the price is really lower than usual.

1962
03:02:10,160 --> 03:02:16,560
Same here. Sometimes shops increase the price first, then call it a deal.

1963
03:02:16,560 --> 03:02:22,640
That's true. You have to compare the cost and value carefully.

1964
03:02:22,640 --> 03:02:27,200
Exactly. A cheap product isn't good if the quality is poor.

1965
03:02:27,200 --> 03:02:32,880
I once bought something on sale and never used it. It was a waste of money.

1966
03:02:32,880 --> 03:02:34,479
I've done that, too.

1967
03:02:34,479 --> 03:02:37,680
Now I try not to buy things I don't need.

1968
03:02:37,680 --> 03:02:43,600
Look at this offer. Buy one item and get the second at half price.

1969
03:02:43,600 --> 03:02:48,720
That's interesting, but only if you really want both items.

1970
03:02:48,720 --> 03:02:53,439
You're right. Shopping smartly means thinking before you spend.

1971
03:02:53,439 --> 03:02:57,920
Yes, good shopping habits help you save money in the long term.

1972
03:02:57,920 --> 03:03:04,399
A good deal should make life easier, not more stressful.

1973
03:03:04,399 --> 03:03:08,479
Rose, have you ever needed to return something you bought?

1974
03:03:08,479 --> 03:03:13,439
Yes, Nick. Last week, I returned a jacket because the size was wrong.

1975
03:03:13,439 --> 03:03:15,840
Was the assistant helpful?

1976
03:03:15,840 --> 03:03:20,160
She was polite and explained the return policy clearly.

1977
03:03:20,160 --> 03:03:25,439
That's good service. Some stores make returns difficult on purpose.

1978
03:03:25,439 --> 03:03:30,720
True. They ask for the receipt and check the item very carefully.

1979
03:03:30,720 --> 03:03:34,479
I always keep receipts in my pocket just in case.

1980
03:03:34,479 --> 03:03:40,720
Same here. Without proof of purchase, exchanges are usually impossible.

1981
03:03:40,720 --> 03:03:44,240
Did you get a refund or store credit?

1982
03:03:44,240 --> 03:03:49,120
I chose an exchange. I picked another jacket instead.

1983
03:03:49,120 --> 03:03:54,960
That sounds fair. Problems happen, but good communication helps.

1984
03:03:54,960 --> 03:04:00,160
Exactly. Calm behavior makes these situations easier for everyone.

1985
03:04:00,160 --> 03:04:05,279
I agree. Being patient with staff often leads to better results.

1986
03:04:05,279 --> 03:04:12,560
Shopping problems are annoying, but they're easier to solve when you stay polite.

1987
03:04:12,560 --> 03:04:17,279
Rose, do you plan your spending based on your monthly income?

1988
03:04:17,279 --> 03:04:22,880
Yes, Nick. My salary covers rent, food, and transport first.

1989
03:04:22,880 --> 03:04:27,920
That's sensible. I separate my income into budget categories.

1990
03:04:27,920 --> 03:04:33,279
I do the same. It helps me control expenses and avoid loss.

1991
03:04:33,279 --> 03:04:36,240
Do you ever invest your money?

1992
03:04:36,240 --> 03:04:41,120
A little. I put some savings into a small fund for the future.

1993
03:04:41,120 --> 03:04:46,880
That's smart. Many people spend everything and save nothing.

1994
03:04:46,880 --> 03:04:52,000
True. Even a small amount saved regularly can grow over time.

1995
03:04:52,000 --> 03:04:56,399
I try not to waste money on things I don't really need.

1996
03:04:56,399 --> 03:05:01,359
Me too. I used to buy impulsively, but now I think first.

1997
03:05:01,359 --> 03:05:04,080
Do you track your spending daily?

1998
03:05:04,080 --> 03:05:07,600
Yes, especially on food and shopping.

1999
03:05:07,600 --> 03:05:09,920
Small costs add up quickly.

2000
03:05:09,920 --> 03:05:15,040
That's a good habit. Financial awareness gives you control.

2001
03:05:15,040 --> 03:05:23,040
Exactly. Managing money well makes life more stable and less stressful.

2002
03:05:23,040 --> 03:05:28,560
Rose, do you enjoy shopping or do you find it stressful sometimes?

2003
03:05:28,560 --> 03:05:34,560
Honestly, Nick, it depends. When the shop is crowded, I feel a bit rushed.

2004
03:05:34,560 --> 03:05:39,760
I understand. Long cues and loud noise can be annoying.

2005
03:05:39,760 --> 03:05:45,040
Yes, especially when people are aggressive or push their carts everywhere.

2006
03:05:45,040 --> 03:05:50,160
That's true. I prefer shopping early in the morning when it's quiet.

2007
03:05:50,160 --> 03:05:55,040
Me, too. I'm more focused and can choose items more carefully.

2008
03:05:55,040 --> 03:05:59,040
Do you ever buy things you didn't plan to buy?

2009
03:05:59,040 --> 03:06:04,399
Sometimes marketing tricks can be very effective if you're not careful.

2010
03:06:04,399 --> 03:06:10,479
I've noticed that, too. Bright signs and special offers catch attention quickly.

2011
03:06:10,479 --> 03:06:15,920
Exactly. But I try not to be influenced too easily anymore.

2012
03:06:15,920 --> 03:06:19,600
Have you ever forgotten something important at the store?

2013
03:06:19,600 --> 03:06:24,000
Yes. I once missed buying milk and had to return later.

2014
03:06:24,000 --> 03:06:28,560
That's annoying. Small mistakes can waste time and energy.

2015
03:06:28,560 --> 03:06:36,880
True. Good shopping habits make daily life smoother and less tiring.

2016
03:06:36,880 --> 03:06:41,680
Rose, shopping habits have changed a lot compared to when we were younger.

2017
03:06:41,680 --> 03:06:47,279
Yes, Nick. People used to shop locally, but now shopping is everywhere.

2018
03:06:47,279 --> 03:06:54,319
That's true. Online shopping feels strange at first, but people get used to it.

2019
03:06:54,319 --> 03:06:59,120
I was scared initially, but now it's convenient and saves time.

2020
03:06:59,120 --> 03:07:04,479
Still, some situations are frightening, like losing your card or wallet.

2021
03:07:04,479 --> 03:07:10,160
Absolutely. That's why I stay alert and protect my personal information.

2022
03:07:10,160 --> 03:07:14,240
Do you think people today spend more than before?

2023
03:07:14,240 --> 03:07:19,760
Probably. Marketing is intense and people want things immediately.

2024
03:07:19,760 --> 03:07:25,600
I agree. Sometimes people buy things just to feel better for a moment.

2025
03:07:25,600 --> 03:07:28,800
Yes, but that feeling doesn't last long.

2026
03:07:28,800 --> 03:07:31,040
Smart choices matter more.

2027
03:07:31,040 --> 03:07:35,760
I've learned that money is a tool, not a goal in life.

2028
03:07:35,760 --> 03:07:41,040
Exactly. It should support your needs, not control your decisions.

2029
03:07:41,040 --> 03:07:45,680
If we shop calmly and thoughtfully, we make better choices.

2030
03:07:45,680 --> 03:07:50,640
I couldn't agree more. Being aware helps us avoid regret later.

2031
03:07:50,640 --> 03:07:57,840
In the end, good shopping habits bring balance and peace of mind.

2032
03:07:57,840 --> 03:08:04,319
Hey, Rose. Good morning. I didn't expect to see you so early on the university campus today.

2033
03:08:04,319 --> 03:08:10,399
Hi, Nick. I have an important lecture this morning in the lecture hall near the science department.

2034
03:08:10,399 --> 03:08:15,279
That sounds interesting. Which subject are you studying this semester?

2035
03:08:15,279 --> 03:08:22,479
I'm taking a biology course in the faculty of science. The laboratory work is really exciting.

2036
03:08:22,479 --> 03:08:29,040
Wow, that must be challenging. Do you spend a lot of time in the lab and the library?

2037
03:08:29,040 --> 03:08:47,439
Yes, almost every day. I usually study in the library after class and sometimes stay late in the laboratory. I remember when I first started college, I felt a little lost on campus. There were so many buildings like the dormatory, the academy, and different institutes.

2038
03:08:47,439 --> 03:08:54,479
I felt the same way. But after a few weeks, I learned where every classroom and department was located.

2039
03:08:54,479 --> 03:09:02,640
That's true. University life is very different from school. The campus feels like a small city full of students.

2040
03:09:02,640 --> 03:09:11,120
Exactly. Education at this level gives us many opportunities to learn new ideas and explore different subjects.

2041
03:09:11,120 --> 03:09:18,640
I agree. Studying at a university helps us build knowledge and prepare for our future careers.

2042
03:09:18,640 --> 03:09:26,880
Well said, Nick. Now, we should hurry to class before the professor begins the lecture.

2043
03:09:26,880 --> 03:09:40,080
Rose, what classes are you taking this semester in your program? I'm following the full curriculum for my biology degree. It includes several subjects and practical workshops.

2044
03:09:40,080 --> 03:09:46,080
That sounds busy. Do you also attend seminars and tutorials during the week?

2045
03:09:46,080 --> 03:09:52,640
Yes, every Tuesday we have a seminar where students discuss new research ideas with the lecturer.

2046
03:09:52,640 --> 03:09:58,640
That must be helpful. I think tutorials are a good way to understand difficult concepts.

2047
03:09:58,640 --> 03:10:06,240
Exactly. In tutorials, the tutor explains the topic step by step and answers questions from students.

2048
03:10:06,240 --> 03:10:10,720
Do you also have special training sessions in your course?

2049
03:10:10,720 --> 03:10:17,279
Yes, sometimes we attend workshops where we practice laboratory techniques and learn new methods.

2050
03:10:17,279 --> 03:10:31,760
That's great preparation for your future qualification. Are you planning to earn a diploma or a full degree? My goal is to complete the degree program first and later I might continue for another certificate in research.

2051
03:10:31,760 --> 03:10:38,560
That sounds like a solid plan. A good education program can open many opportunities.

2052
03:10:38,560 --> 03:10:47,920
I agree, Nick. With the right training and dedication, students can build strong knowledge and useful skills.

2053
03:10:47,920 --> 03:10:54,880
Rose, are you ready for the exam next week? The professor said it will be quite difficult.

2054
03:10:54,880 --> 03:11:00,960
I'm a little nervous, Nick. We already had a quiz yesterday and the final test is coming soon.

2055
03:11:00,960 --> 03:11:07,279
Yes, I remember. The lecturer mentioned that this assessment will cover the whole course.

2056
03:11:07,279 --> 03:11:13,760
That's right. The tutor advised us to review every lecture carefully before the exam.

2057
03:11:13,760 --> 03:11:26,960
Good idea. I usually revise my notes and practice questions from the textbook. Me too. Some students are also preparing together in study groups. It helps a lot.

2058
03:11:26,960 --> 03:11:32,720
Are there any scholarships or awards for students who get the best results?

2059
03:11:32,720 --> 03:11:39,600
Yes, the university offers a scholarship and a special academic prize for outstanding students.

2060
03:11:39,600 --> 03:11:47,760
That's motivating. I would love to graduate with a good result and attend the graduation ceremony proudly.

2061
03:11:47,760 --> 03:11:54,160
Same here. Finishing university and becoming a graduate will be a big achievement.

2062
03:11:54,160 --> 03:12:07,760
Absolutely. All this hard work will help us succeed in our future careers. I hope so. For now, we should focus on studying and passing the exam first.

2063
03:12:07,760 --> 03:12:11,840
Rose, the library is very quiet today.

2064
03:12:11,840 --> 03:12:15,120
It's a perfect place to concentrate on our study.

2065
03:12:15,120 --> 03:12:21,760
I agree, Nick. A quiet environment helps me focus and remember important information.

2066
03:12:21,760 --> 03:12:24,000
What are you reading right now?

2067
03:12:24,000 --> 03:12:30,960
I'm studying a chapter about human biology. It explains many facts and scientific data.

2068
03:12:30,960 --> 03:12:37,840
Interesting. Does the textbook include figures and numbers to explain the topic?

2069
03:12:37,840 --> 03:12:44,479
Yes, it includes many diagrams and detailed figures that make the information easier to understand.

2070
03:12:44,479 --> 03:12:51,040
That's helpful. Sometimes I write important details in my notebook so I don't forget them.

2071
03:12:51,040 --> 03:12:56,640
Good strategy. Memory improves when we review information regularly.

2072
03:12:56,640 --> 03:13:03,520
I also think knowledge grows when we combine facts with real understanding.

2073
03:13:03,520 --> 03:13:09,840
Exactly. Wisdom comes from studying deeply and thinking carefully about what we learn.

2074
03:13:09,840 --> 03:13:23,359
Education really helps us develop our abilities and skills. That's true. The more we learn, the more capable we become in solving problems.

2075
03:13:23,359 --> 03:13:28,640
Rose, what are you working on now? It looks like a serious project.

2076
03:13:28,640 --> 03:13:33,439
Yes, Nick. I'm preparing a research paper for my biology course.

2077
03:13:33,439 --> 03:13:38,160
That sounds important. What is the main idea of your research?

2078
03:13:38,160 --> 03:13:44,560
My project explores a new concept about plant growth and environmental conditions.

2079
03:13:44,560 --> 03:13:49,520
Interesting. Are you using any scientific theories in your study?

2080
03:13:49,520 --> 03:13:56,960
Yes. The professor suggested that we connect our research with existing theories from recent articles and journals.

2081
03:13:56,960 --> 03:14:01,040
Do you read many academic journals for your research?

2082
03:14:01,040 --> 03:14:08,319
I do. I also check textbooks and sometimes magazines that discuss scientific discoveries.

2083
03:14:08,319 --> 03:14:12,319
I see you have a notebook full of notes and summaries.

2084
03:14:12,319 --> 03:14:19,600
Yes, I write short summaries for every article I read so I can organize my ideas clearly.

2085
03:14:19,600 --> 03:14:25,200
That's a smart method. Writing helps us understand information more deeply.

2086
03:14:25,200 --> 03:14:33,359
Exactly. A good research paper should combine clear ideas, reliable information, and careful study. Pause.

2087
03:14:33,359 --> 03:14:35,600
Two fours. Pause.

2088
03:14:35,600 --> 03:14:46,399
Rose, today's lecture about scientific experiments was really interesting. I agree, Nick. The professor explained the method very clearly.

2089
03:14:46,399 --> 03:14:52,239
Yes. He started by asking a simple question about how the experiment works.

2090
03:14:52,239 --> 03:14:58,080
Then he gave a detailed explanation and a clear definition of the main concept.

2091
03:14:58,080 --> 03:15:03,520
I liked how he compared different systems to help us understand the process.

2092
03:15:03,520 --> 03:15:15,920
That comparison made the theory easier to follow. It was a good example of effective teaching. After that he demonstrated the experiment step by step in the laboratory.

2093
03:15:15,920 --> 03:15:20,960
Right? And the students carefully observed the result of each step.

2094
03:15:20,960 --> 03:15:28,319
The analysis of the data was also interesting. It helped us see how the experiment leads to a conclusion.

2095
03:15:28,319 --> 03:15:41,040
Exactly. Scientific discovery often comes from careful observation and analysis. I think discussions like this help students understand difficult topics more clearly.

2096
03:15:41,040 --> 03:15:49,520
I agree. Asking questions and sharing answers makes learning much more effective.

2097
03:15:49,520 --> 03:15:54,399
Rose, how do you usually prepare for an important exam?

2098
03:15:54,399 --> 03:16:01,200
I start by making a study plan. It helps me organize my time and focus on each subject.

2099
03:16:01,200 --> 03:16:08,160
That's a good strategy. I usually review my notes and revise the most difficult topics first.

2100
03:16:08,160 --> 03:16:14,960
I do the same. After reviewing the material, I practice answering questions from previous tests.

2101
03:16:14,960 --> 03:16:23,359
Practice really helps improve understanding. Sometimes I also write short summaries to remember key ideas.

2102
03:16:23,359 --> 03:16:29,600
Yes, writing helps a lot. I also record important points so I can review them later.

2103
03:16:29,600 --> 03:16:33,760
Do you ever present your ideas to classmates when studying?

2104
03:16:33,760 --> 03:16:39,359
Sometimes explaining a topic to someone else helps me understand it better.

2105
03:16:39,359 --> 03:16:46,319
That's true. When we discuss and describe ideas, our knowledge becomes clearer.

2106
03:16:46,319 --> 03:16:53,120
Exactly. Studying regularly helps us develop better learning habits and academic skills.

2107
03:16:53,120 --> 03:16:58,160
And with enough effort, we can improve our progress throughout the semester.

2108
03:16:58,160 --> 03:17:07,439
Right. Success in education often comes from consistent practice and careful preparation.

2109
03:17:07,439 --> 03:17:14,399
Rose, can you believe our graduation is coming soon? It feels like we just started university.

2110
03:17:14,399 --> 03:17:21,040
I know, Nick. Over the years, we have learned so much and developed many new skills.

2111
03:17:21,040 --> 03:17:28,960
Yes. From the beginning, we had to calculate data, measure results, and design experiments for our projects.

2112
03:17:28,960 --> 03:17:36,800
That's true. Sometimes we even had to create new ideas and invent solutions to difficult problems.

2113
03:17:36,800 --> 03:17:44,000
I remember making many mistakes during my first year, but checking and correcting them helped me improve.

2114
03:17:44,000 --> 03:17:55,439
Exactly. Progress often comes from learning from our mistakes. Fortunately, we passed most of our courses. A few students had to repeat some classes, though.

2115
03:17:55,439 --> 03:18:02,800
That happens sometimes. Education can be challenging, but persistence helps students succeed.

2116
03:18:02,800 --> 03:18:08,239
The most important thing is understanding what we study, not just memorizing it.

2117
03:18:08,239 --> 03:18:21,840
I agree. When we truly understand something, we can remember it for a long time. And when we concentrate and focus on learning, we become more confident in our abilities.

2118
03:18:21,840 --> 03:18:28,160
That's right. Graduation will be the result of years of hard work and dedication.

2119
03:18:28,160 --> 03:18:32,800
I'm excited to see what the future brings after university.

2120
03:18:32,800 --> 03:18:41,359
Me too, Nick. Our education is just the beginning of a lifelong journey of learning.

2121
03:18:41,359 --> 03:18:48,319
Rose, when I look back at our time at university, I feel grateful for everything we learned.

2122
03:18:48,319 --> 03:18:56,319
Me too, Nick. Education is not only about exams and grades, but also about understanding the world.

2123
03:18:56,319 --> 03:19:02,319
That's true. Our studies helped us develop knowledge, skills, and confidence.

2124
03:19:02,319 --> 03:19:08,479
Yes. And we also learned how to think critically and analyze different ideas.

2125
03:19:08,479 --> 03:19:15,120
I think good education can change people's lives and even improve society worldwide.

2126
03:19:15,120 --> 03:19:22,560
Absolutely. When people gain knowledge and wisdom, they can solve problems and create new opportunities.

2127
03:19:22,560 --> 03:19:27,600
Sometimes the journey was difficult, but every challenge helped us grow stronger.

2128
03:19:27,600 --> 03:19:33,520
And every lesson, lecture, and discussion helped us discover new perspectives.

2129
03:19:33,520 --> 03:19:39,520
I hope we continue learning even after graduation. Learning should never stop.

2130
03:19:39,520 --> 03:19:47,120
I agree completely. Education is a lifelong process and curiosity keeps our minds active.

2131
03:19:47,120 --> 03:19:52,800
Well said, Rose. The future is full of possibilities for people who love learning.

2132
03:19:52,800 --> 03:20:00,640
Exactly, Nick. Let's keep exploring knowledge and building a better future.

2133
03:20:00,640 --> 03:20:13,439
Good morning, Rose. I didn't expect to see you so early at the park running track today. Hi, Nick. I started a new fitness routine, so I come here every morning for exercise.

2134
03:20:13,439 --> 03:20:19,120
That sounds like a great habit. Do you usually run or jog around the track?

2135
03:20:19,120 --> 03:20:24,880
I normally jog for 20 minutes, then walk slowly to relax my muscles.

2136
03:20:24,880 --> 03:20:27,920
That is a good way to train your body.

2137
03:20:27,920 --> 03:20:32,800
Regular exercise really improves strength and energy.

2138
03:20:32,800 --> 03:20:40,399
Exactly. My trainer at the gym says movement and stretching are very important before any workout.

2139
03:20:40,399 --> 03:20:46,160
Do you also practice other activities like cycling or swimming during the week?

2140
03:20:46,160 --> 03:20:53,200
Yes, sometimes I ride my bicycle near the river and on weekends I swim at the sports center.

2141
03:20:53,200 --> 03:21:01,120
That sounds very healthy. Many athletes say variety in training helps improve speed and balance.

2142
03:21:01,120 --> 03:21:08,640
I agree. Exercise also helps reduce stress and keeps both the body and mind strong.

2143
03:21:08,640 --> 03:21:14,960
Well, since we are both here, maybe we can jog together around the field.

2144
03:21:14,960 --> 03:21:22,960
Great idea, Nick. Let's start slowly and warm up before we run faster.

2145
03:21:22,960 --> 03:21:29,760
Rose, after our jog yesterday, I watched an exciting sport match at the city stadium.

2146
03:21:29,760 --> 03:21:32,720
Really? What kind of game was it, Nick?

2147
03:21:32,720 --> 03:21:35,760
Was it football or another competition?

2148
03:21:35,760 --> 03:21:43,279
It was a football match between two strong teams and the players were incredibly fast and skilled.

2149
03:21:43,279 --> 03:21:52,640
That sounds exciting. I always enjoy watching athletes compete because their strength and energy are impressive.

2150
03:21:52,640 --> 03:22:06,720
Yes, the coach and trainer worked closely with the team during the warm-up before the match began. I think warm-up exercises and stretching help athletes prepare their muscles and prevent injuries.

2151
03:22:06,720 --> 03:22:08,399
Exactly.

2152
03:22:08,399 --> 03:22:14,479
During the game, the referee had to watch every movement and action very carefully.

2153
03:22:14,479 --> 03:22:22,479
I can imagine in a big competition or race, even a small mistake can change the result.

2154
03:22:22,479 --> 03:22:28,800
One player on the field showed amazing speed and balance while running with the ball.

2155
03:22:28,800 --> 03:22:34,640
That kind of performance usually comes from years of training, practice, and discipline.

2156
03:22:34,640 --> 03:22:43,200
You are right. Professional athletes train every day to improve their power, flexibility, and overall performance.

2157
03:22:43,200 --> 03:22:51,200
Watching sports like that always inspires me to keep exercising and staying active.

2158
03:22:51,200 --> 03:22:59,359
Rose, after exercising regularly, I realized that diet and nutrition are just as important as workouts.

2159
03:22:59,359 --> 03:23:07,040
I completely agree, Nick. A healthy diet gives our body the energy and nutrients it needs every day.

2160
03:23:07,040 --> 03:23:13,439
Lately, I have been paying attention to calories, protein, and vitamins in the food I eat.

2161
03:23:13,439 --> 03:23:21,520
That is a good idea. Foods like fruit, vegetables, and whole grains provide many important minerals and fiber.

2162
